Ethamsylate is a haemostatic drug, which inhibits biosynthesis and action of prostaglandins, and increases capillary endothelial resistance as and platelet adhesion.
Cyromazine is a triazine insect growth regulator used as an insecticide and an acaricide.
Nefopam HCl is an centrally-acting but non-opioid analgesic drug by blocking voltage-gated sodium channel and inhibition of serotonin, dopamine and noradrenaline reuptake.
Betamipron is a chemical compound which is used together with panipenem to inhibit panipenem uptake into the renal tubule and prevent nephrotoxicity.
Clofibric acid is a PPARα agonist and hypolipidemic agent.
Erythritol is a sugar alcohol used as low-calorie sweetener.
Mexiletine HCl belongs to Class IB anti-arrhythmic group of medicines, inhibits sodium channels to reduce the inward sodium current.

Cepharanthine is a biscoclaurine alkaloid inhibiting tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-α-mediated NFκB stimulation, plasma membrane lipid peroxidation and platelet aggregation and suppressing cytokine production.
SC144 is an orally active small-molecule gp130 inhibitor.
4E1RCat is a dual inhibitor of eIF4E:eIF4G and eIF4E:4E-BP1 interaction, and inhibits the binding of eIF4G to eIF4E with IC50 of 3.2 μM.
(S)-crizotinib, the (S)-enantiomer of crizotinib, is a potent MTH1 (NUDT1) inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM.
Gabapentin Hydrochloride is a GABA analogue.
Norfloxacin (Norxacin) is a broad-spectrum antibiotic.
Ketoprofen (Actron) is a non-selective NSAID with IC50 of 0.5 μM and 2.33 μM for human recombinant COX-1 and COX-2, respectively.
Fluorometholone Acetate is a synthetic corticosteroid, used in the treatment of steroid responsive inflammatory conditions of the eye.
Bergapten is a psoralen that can be photoactivated and is capable of crossing-linking DNA, covalently modifying proteins and lipids, and consequently inhibiting cell replication.
Thiamet G is a potent, selective O-GlcNAcase inhibitor with Kiof 21 nM, while exhibiting 37,000-fold selectivity over human lysosomal –hexosaminidase.
PTC-209 is a potent and selective BMI-1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 μM, and results in irreversible reduction of cancer-initiating cells (CICs).
VGX-1027 is an orally active immunomodulator. Phase 1.
Biapenem is a carbapenem antibiotic.
Cidofovir(Vistide) is an injectable antiviral medication for the treatment of cytomegalovirus (CMV) retinitis. (IC50= 0.94 μM).
Ketorolac (Ketorolac tromethamine) is a non-selective COX inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 1.23 μM and 3.50 μM, respectively.
Oxybuprocaine HCl is a local anesthetic, which is used especially in ophthalmology and otolaryngology.
Cetrimonium Bromide is a known component of the broad-spectrum antiseptic cetrimide, which is a mixture of different quaternary ammonium salts.
OAC1 (Oct4-activating compound 1) can enhance the efficiency of reprogramming.
CGP 57380 is potent MNK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 2.2 μM, exhibiting no inhibitory activity on p38, JNK1, ERK1 and -2, PKC, or c-Src-like kinases.
Y-320 is an orally active immunomodulator, and inhibits IL-17 production by CD4 T cells stimulated with IL-15 with IC50 of 20 to 60 nM.
Minoxidil is a vasodilator medication known for its ability to slow or stop hair loss and promote hair regrowth.
Ibuprofen Lysine(Motrin) is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.
Betamethasone Dipropionate is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive abilities.

Oxaprozin is a non-narcotic, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to relieve the inflammation, swelling, stiffness, and joint pain associated with osteoarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis.
Sodium Ascorbate is a more bioavailable form of vitamin C that is an alternative to taking ascorbic acid as a supplement.
4μ8C is a potent and selective IRE1 Rnase inhibitor with IC50 of 76 nM.
NH125 is a selective eEF-2 kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM, >125-fold selectivity over PKC, PKA, and CaMKII, and also a potent histidine kinase inhibitor.
AZD7545 is a potent PDHK inhibitor with IC50 of 36.8 nM and 6.4 nM for PDHK1 and PDHK2, respectively.
Teicoplanin is an antibiotic used in the prophylaxis.
Alendronate Sodium (Fosamax) is a farnesyl diphosphate synthase inhibitor with IC50 of 460 nM.
Betamethasone Valerate is a moderately potent glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.
Pilocarpine HCl is a nonselective muscarinic acetylcholine receptor agonist used to produce an experimental model of epilepsy.
Bromfenac is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID), which has anti-inflammatory activity and may block prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cyclooxygenase 1 and 2.
TTNPB (Arotinoid Acid) is a potent RAR agonist, and inhibits binding of [3H]tRA with IC50 of 5.1 nM, 4.5 nM, and 9.3 nM for human RARα, β, and γ, respectively.
STF-118804 is a highly specific NAMPT inhibitor.
Sal003 is a potent and cell-permeable eIF-2α phosphatase inhibitor.

Dynasore is a cell-permeable, reversible non-competitive dynamin inhibitor of GTPase activity of dynamin 1/2, with IC50 of 15 μM, also inhibits the mitochondrial dynamin Drp1, with no effect against other small GTPase.
Risedronate sodium is a bisphosphonate used to strengthen bone, treat or prevent osteoporosis, and treat Paget's disease of bone.
Naproxen is a COX inhibitor for COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 8.7 μM and 5.2 μM, respectively.
Eplerenone (Inspra) is an aldosterone antagonist with an IC50 of 0.36 μM.
Nithiamide is a non-5-nitroimidazole drugs.
Sulfamethoxypyridazine is a long-acting sulfonamide for treatment of Dermatitis herpetiformis.

Tamibarotene, also called retinobenzoic acid, is orally active, synthetic retinoid, developed to overcome all-trans retinoic acid (ATRA) resistance, with potential antineoplastic activity against acute promyelocytic leukaemia (APL) .
NXY-059 is a novel nitrone, shows efficacious neuroprotective effects.
Atglistatin is a highly potent, and selective inhibitor of adipose triglyceride lipase (ATGL) with IC50 of 0.7 μM, high selectivity over other key metabolic lipases.
ZLN005 is a potent and tissue-specific PGC-1α transcriptional activator.
RI-1 is a RAD51 inhibitor with IC50 ranging from 5 to 30 μM.
Ofloxacin is a synthetic broad-spectrum antimicrobial agent.

Docosanol is a saturated fatty alcoholused traditionally as an emollient, emulsifier, and thickener in cosmetics, nutritional supplement. (ED50=2.5 mg/ml for plaque inhibition, and ED50=1.7 mg/ml for inhibition of virus production)
Eplerenone is an aldosterone antagonist with an IC50 of 0.36 μM.
Zoxazolamine is a centrally acting myorelaxant, which is formerly used as an antispasmodic and uricosuric.
Mechlorethamine is the prototype of alkylating agents, it works by binding to DNA, crosslinking two strands and preventing cell duplication.
T0901317 is a potent and selective agonist for both LXR and FXR, with EC50 of ~50 nM and 5 μM, respectively.
AdipoRon is a novel, and orally bioavailable adiponectin receptor agonist with KD of 1.8 and 3.1 μM for AdipoR1 and AdipoR2, respectively.
FH1(BRD-K4477) is a small molecule, which promotes differentiation of iPS-derived hepatocytes.
Ellagic acid has antiproliferative and antioxidant property.
Cefaclor is a cephalosporin antibiotic.
Ibuprofen (Dolgesic) is an anti-inflammatory inhibitor targeting COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 13 μM and 370 μM, respectively.
Piroxicam (Feldene) is a non-selective COX inhibitor with an IC50 of 6 mM.
Phenazopyridine HCl a local analgesic that has been used in urinary tract disorders.
Epinastine is an antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer that is used in eye drops to treat allergic conjunctivitis.
Cilengitide is a potent integrin inhibitor for αvβ3 receptor and αvβ5 receptor with IC50 of 4.1 nM and 79 nM, respectively; ~10-fold selectivity against gpIIbIIIa. Phase 2.
4EGI-1 is a competitive eIF4E/eIF4G interaction inhibitor by binding to eIF4E with KD of 25 μM.
FPH1 (BRD-6125) is a small molecule, which promotes expansion of iPS-derived hepatocytes.
Etodolac (Lodine) is a COX inhibitor with an IC50 of 53.5 nM.
Perindopril Erbumine(Aceon) is the tert-butylamine salt of perindopril, the ethyl ester of a non-sulfhydryl angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor.
Methyldopa (Aldomet) is a DOPA decarboxylase competitive inhibitor with an ED50 of 21.8 mg/kg.
Paliperidone (Invega) is an atypical antipsychotic.
Levodopa (Sinemet) is an amino acid precursor of dopamine with antiparkinsonian properties.
Clofibrate (Atromid-S), a fibric acid derivative used in the treatment of hyperlipoproteinemia type III and severe hypertriglyceridemia.
Adenine is a purine derivative and a nucleobase with a variety of roles in biochemistry.
Ciprofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic, shows broad and potent antibacterial activity, with MIC90 of 0.024-6 μM. Phase 4.
Fosinopril sodium (Monopril) is the ester prodrug of an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension and some types of chronic heart failure.
Asaraldehyde is a natural COX-2 inhibitor, exhibiting 17-fold selectivity over COX-1.
Acemetacin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and a glycolic acid ester of indometacin that is a cyclooxygenase inhibitor.
Fenoprofen calcium hydrate (Nalfon) is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID).
Amikacin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections._x000D_
Ampiroxicam is a nonselective cyclooxygenase inhibitor uesd as anti-inflammatory drug.
Esomeprazole magnesium is a proton pump inhibitor to reduce gastric acid secretion.
Betaxolol is a β1 adrenergic receptor blocker with IC50 of 6 μM.
Adenine sulfate is a sulfate salt form of adenine which is a purine derivative and a nucleobase with a variety of roles in biochemistry.
Nimesulide is a relatively COX-2 selective inhibitor with IC50 of 26 μM.
Flunixin meglumine is a potent inhibitor of the enzyme cyclooxygenase used as analgesic agent with anti-inflammatory and antipyretic activity.
Riboflavin (vitamin B2) is an easily absorbed micronutrient with a key role in maintaining health in humans and other animals.
Ethisterone is a progestogen hormone being considered to treat prostate cancer.
Niclosamide can inhibit DNA replication and inhibit STAT with IC50 of 0.7 μM.
Ibandronate is a highly potent nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate used for the treatment of osteoporosis.

Monofluorophosphate is a competitive inhibitor of pyruvate kinase and alkaline phosphatase with Ki of 3.4 mM and 69 μM, respectively, which also irreversibly inhibits phosphorylase phosphatase with Ki of 0.5 mM.
L-Glutamine is one of the 20 amino acids encoded by the standard genetic code.
Penicillamine(Cuprimine, Depen) is used as an antirheumatic and as a chelating agent in Wilson’s disease.
ATP is a disodium salt form of adenosine-triphosphate which is a multifunctional nucleoside triphosphate.
Lornoxicam is a COX-1 and COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM and 8 nM, respectively.
Licofelone is a dual COX/LOX inhibitor being considered as a treatment for osteoarthritis.
Cefprozil hydrate (Cefzil) is a second-generation cephalosporin type antibiotic.

Peramivir Trihydrate is a trihydrate of the anti-infection agent peramivir (RWJ-270201,BCX-1812) which is a transition-state analogue and a potent, specific influenza viral neuraminidase inhibitor with an IC50 of median 0.09 nM.
Droxidopa (L-DOPS) is a psychoactive drug and acts as a prodrug to the neurotransmitters norepinephrine (noradrenaline) and epinephrine (adrenaline).

Naftifine is an allylamine antifungal drug for the topical treatment of tinea pedis, tinea cruris, and tinea corporis, probably involves selectively blocking sterol biosynthesis via inhibition of the squalene 2,3-epoxidase enzyme.
Colistin is a cyclic cationic decapeptide linked to a fatty acid side chain, it belongs to a group of similarly structured bacterial antimicrobial peptides.
Oxybutynin (Ditropan) is an anticholinergic medication used to relieve urinary and bladder difficulties.
Etidronate (Didronel) is a human protein tyrosine phosphatase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM.
Liranaftate is a squalene epoxidase inhibitor with anti-fungicidal activities.
Clindamycin phosphate is a lincosamide antibiotic for Plasmodium falciparum with IC50 of 12 nM.
Fudosteine is a novel mucoactive agent and a MUC5AC mucin hypersecretion inhibitor.
Oxacillin sodium monohydrate is an antibacterial agent and is a narrow spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class.
ML130 is a potent and selective inhibitor of NOD1 with IC50 of 0.56 μM, inhibits NF-κB activation, exhibits 36-fold selectivity over NOD2.
Rofecoxib is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM.
Abacavir is a commonly used nucleoside analogue with potent antiviral activity against HIV-1.
Bismuth Subsalicylate is the active ingredient in Pepto-Bismol and inhibits prostaglandin G/H Synthase 1/2.

The thiopurine drugs are purine antimetabolites widely used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia, autoimmune disorders (e.g., Crohn's disease, rheumatoid arthritis) and organ transplant recipients.
Risedronic acid (Actonel) is a bisphosphonate used to strengthen bone, treat or prevent osteoporosis, and treat Paget's disease of bone.
D-Cycloserine is an analog of the amino acid D-alanine.
Oxytetracycline Dihydrate is a prescription antibiotic, iinterfering with the ability of bacteria to produce essential proteins.
Fleroxacin (Quinodis) is a new broad-spectrum fluoroquinolone.
Neomycin sulphate belongs to a class of antibiotics known as the aminoglycosides.
Lumiracoxib is a novel, selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of 0.14 μM and 0.06 μM, exhibits 515-fold selectivity over COX-1. Phase 4.
Besifloxacin HCl is a fourth-generation fluoroquinolone antibiotic.
L-Arginine is the nitrogen donor for synthesis of nitric oxide, a potent vasodilator that is deficient during times of sickle cell crisis.
Valdecoxib is a potent and selective inhibitor of COX-2 with IC50 of 5 nM.
Verteporfin(Visudyne), a benzoporphyrin derivative, is a medication used as a photosensitizer for photodynamic therapy.
Diclofenac Sodium is a non-selective COX inhibitor with IC50 of 60 and 220 nM for ovine COX-1 and -2, respectively.

Sodium orthovanadate is the chemical compound Na3VO4 and contains the tetrahedral VO43. It is an inhibitor of protein tyrosine phosphatases, alkaline phosphatases and a number of ATPases, most likely acting as a phosphate analogue.
Mitiglinide is a blood glucose-lowering drugs, stimulating insulin secretion by closing the ATP-sensitive K+ channels in pancreatic beta-cells.
Sulfadoxine(Sulphadoxine) is an ultra-long-lasting sulfonamide with an IC50 of 249 μg/ml for P. vivax
Prednisolone Acetate is a synthetic corticosteroid drug that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant agent.

Hygromycin B, a selective antibiotic that is effective on most bacteria, fungi and higher eukaryotes, inhibits protein synthesis by interfering with translocation and causing mistranslation at the 70S ribosome.
Danofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibacterial for veterinary use, with MIC90 of 0.28 μM.
Triflusal irreversibly inhibits the production of thromboxane-B2 in platelets by acetylating cycloxygenase-1.
Nabumetone is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and its active metabolite inhibits the COX.
Bacitracin zinc is a dephosphorylation of the C55-isoprenyl pyrophosphate interference for inhibition of cleavage of Tyr from Met-enkephalin with IC50 of 10 μM.
Disodium Cromoglycate is an antiallergic drug with IC50 of 39 μg/mL.
Taurine, or 2-aminoethanesulfonic acid, is an organic acid.

Lisinopril is angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor, used in treatment of hypertension, congestive heart failure, and heart attacks, and also in preventing renal and retinal complications of diabetes.
Tobramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic with an IC50 of 9.7 μM
Phenacetin is a non-opioid analgesic without anti-inflammatory properties.
Zaltoprofen is an inhibitor of Cox-1 and Cox-2 for treatment of arthritis.
Amikacin sulfate binds to 16S rRNA (bacterial 30S ribosome), causing misreading of mRNA and supressing proteins synthesis.
Thiamine or vitamin B1 is a water-soluble vitamin of the B complex, its phosphate derivatives are involved in many cellular processes.
Netilmicin Sulfate is a member of the aminoglycoside family of antibiotics.
Amlodipine (Norvasc) is a long-acting calcium channel blocker with an IC50 of 1.9 nM.
Tolfenamic acid is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM.
Pramipexole is a partial/full D2S, D2L, D3, D4, receptor agonist with a Ki of 3.9, 2.2, 0.5, 5.1 nM.
Dexmedetomidine is a highly selective and potent alpha-2 adrenoceptor agonist, which reduces anesthetic requirements for patients by providing significant sedation.
DL-Adrenaline is a hormone and a neurotransmitter secreted by the medulla of the adrenal glands.
Calcium levofolinate (Calcium Folinate) is a calcium salt of folinic acid that is an adjuvant used in cancer chemotherapy.
Bufexamac is a COX inhibitor for IFN-α release with EC50 of 8.9 μM.
Creatinine is a break-down product of creatine phosphate in muscle, and is usually produced at a fairly constant rate by the body._x000D_
Clinafloxacin (PD127391) is a fluoroquinolone that inhibits both DNA gyrase and topoisomerase IV dually in Streptococcus pneumoniae.
Erythromycin Ethylsuccinate, an oral macrolide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces erythreus, reversibly binds to the 50S ribosome of bacteria, and inhibits protein synthesis.
Dequalinium Chloride is a PKC inhibitor with IC50 of 7-18 μM, and also a selective blocker of apamin-sensitive K+ channels with IC50 of 1.1 μM.
Sevelamer HCl is a phosphate binding drug used to treat hyperphosphatemia via binding to dietary phosphate and prevents its absorption.
EUK 134, a synthetic superoxide dismutase (SOD)/catalase mimetic, exhibits potent antioxidant activities, and inhibits the formation of β-amyloid and related amyloid fibril.
Deferiprone is a chelating agent with an affinity for ferric ion (iron III), binds with ferric ions to form neutral 3:1 (deferiprone:iron) complexes that are stable over a wide range of pH values.
Decoquinate is a coccidiostat.
Hexamethonium Bromide is a selective antagonist of neuronal-type nicotinic AChR in ganglia.
Azithromycin Dihydrate is an acid stable orally administered macrolide antimicrobial drug, structurally related to erythromycin.
Mefenamic acid is a competitive inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2.
D-Phenylalanine, an carboxypeptidase A, endorphinase and enkephalinase inhibitor, enhances endorphin production and diminishes pain.
Bismuth Subcitrate is an antibiotic used to treat stomach ulcers associated with Helicobacter pylori, a bacterial infection.
Sodium gluconate is the sodium salt of gluconic acid widely used in food and pharmaceutical industry.
Tetramisole is a mixture of dextro- and levo isomers used as an anthelmintic.
Amoxapine is a tricyclic dibenzoxazepine (an N-aryl piperazine) which acts similarly to several other tricyclic antidepressants, amoxapine inhibits GLYT2a transport activity with IC50 of 92 μM.
Clodronate Disodium, a bisphosphonate, is a potent antiosteolytic agent which inhibits bone resorption.

Minocycline HCl is the most lipid soluble and most active tetracycline antibiotic, binds to the 30S ribosomal subunit, preventing the binding of tRNA to the mRNA-ribosome complex and interfering with protein synthesis.
Histamine acts directly on the blood vessels to dilate arteries and capillaries mediated by both H 1- and H 2-receptors.
Deoxycorticosterone acetate is a steroid hormone used for intramuscular injection for replacement therapy of the adrenocortical steroid.

Linifanib (ABT-869) is a novel, potent ATP-competitive VEGFR/PDGFR inhibitor for KDR, CSF-1R, Flt-1/3 and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 4 nM, 3 nM, 3 nM/4 nM and 66 nM respectively, mostly effective in mutant kinase-dependent cancer cells (i.e. FLT3). Phase 3.

Cediranib (AZD2171) is a highly potent VEGFR(KDR) inhibitor with IC50 of <1 nM, also inhibits Flt1/4 with IC50 of 5 nM/≤3 nM, similar activity against c-Kit and PDGFRβ, 36-, 110-fold and >1000-fold selective more for VEGFR than PDGFR-α, CSF-1R and Flt3, Phase 2/3.
Imatinib Mesylate (STI571) is an orally bioavailability mesylate salt of Imatinib, which is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM, respectively.
Rapamycin (Sirolimus, AY-22989, WY-090217) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of ~0.1 nM.
Enzastaurin (LY317615) is a potent PKCβ selective inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM, 6- to 20-fold selectivity against PKCα, PKCγ and PKCε. Phase 3.
SB216763 is a potent and selective GSK-3 inhibitor with IC50 of 34.3 nM for GSK-3α and equally effective at inhibiting human GSK-3β.
KU-55933 is a potent and specific ATM inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 12.9 nM/2.2 nM, and is highly selective for ATM as compared to DNA-PK, PI3K/PI4K, ATR and mTOR.

LY294002 is the first synthetic molecule known to inhibit PI3Kα/δ/β with IC50 of 0.5 μM/0.57 μM/0.97 μM, respectively; more stable in solution than Wortmannin, and also blocks autophagosome formation.
JNJ-38877605 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met with IC50 of 4 nM, 600-fold selective for c-Met than 200 other tyrosine and serine-threonine kinases. Phase 1.
AT9283 is a potent JAK2/3 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM/1.1 nM; also potent to Aurora A/B, Abl(T315I). Phase 1/2.
Axitinib is a multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ and c-Kit with IC50 of 0.1 nM, 0.2 nM, 0.1-0.3 nM, 1.6 nM and 1.7 nM, respectively.

Dovitinib (TKI258, CHIR258) is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGF-1R and HER2. Phase 4.
Lapatinib Ditosylate (GW572016, GW2016) is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM, respectively.
Sorafenib Tosylate (Bay 43-9006) is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM, respectively.
AC480 (BMS-599626) is a selective and efficacious inhibitor of HER1 and HER2 with IC50 of 20 nM and 30 nM, ~8-fold less potent to HER4, >100-fold to VEGFR2, c-Kit, Lck, MET etc. Phase 1.
SB203580 is a p38 MAPK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3-0.5 μM, 10-fold less sensitive to SAPK3(106T) and SAPK4(106T) and blocks PKB phosphorylation with IC50 of 3-5 μM.
GSK1904529A is a selective inhibitor of IGF-1R and IR with IC50 of 27 nM and 25 nM, >100-fold more selective for IGF-1R/InsR than Akt1/2, Aurora A/B,B-Raf, CDK2, EGFR etc.
OSU-03012 is a potent inhibitor of recombinant PDK-1 with IC50 of 5 μM and 2-fold increase in potency over OSU-02067.
PD0332991 is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 2/3.
Brivanib alaninate (BMS-582664) is the prodrug of BMS-540215, an ATP-competitive inhibitor against VEGFR2 with IC50 of 25 nM.
Saracatinib (AZD0530) is a potent Src inhibitor with IC50 of 2.7 nM, and potent to c-Yes, Fyn, Lyn, Blk, Fgr and Lck; less active for Abl and EGFR (L858R and L861Q). Phase 1/2.
Canertinib (CI-1033) is a pan-ErbB inhibitor for EGFR and ErbB2 with IC50 of 1.5 nM and 9.0 nM, no activity to PDGFR, FGFR, InsR, PKC, or CDK1/2/4. Phase 3.

Motesanib Diphosphate (AMG-706) is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/3 nM/6 nM, respectively; similar activity against Kit, ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR than PDGFR and Ret. Phase 1/2.
Sunitinib Malate is a multi-targeted RTK inhibitor targeting VEGFR2 (Flk-1) and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 80 nM and 2 nM, and also inhibits c-Kit.
Masitinib is a novel inhibitor for Kit and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 200 nM and 540 nM/800 nM, weak inhibition to ABL and c-Fms. Phase 2/3.
SB202190 (FHPI) is a potent p38 MAPK inhibitor targeting p38α/β with IC50 of 50 nM/100 nM, sometimes used instead of SB 203580 to investigate potential roles for SAPK2a/p38 in vivo.
PF-04217903 is a selective ATP-competitive c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4.8 nM, susceptible to oncogenic mutations (no activity to Y1230C mutant). Phase 1.

Danusertib (PHA-739358) is an Aurora kinase inhibitor for Aurora A/B/C with IC50 of 13 nM/79 nM/61 nM, modestly potent to Abl, TrkA, c-RET and FGFR1, and less potent to Lck, VEGFR2/3, c-Kit, CDK2, etc. Phase 2.

Triciribine is a DNA synthesis inhibitor, also inhibits Akt and HIV-1 with IC50 of 130 nM and 20 nM, respectively; does not inhibit PI3K/PDK1; 5000-fold less active in cells lacking adenosine kinase. Phase 1/2.
AG-490 (Tyrphostin B42) is an inhibitor of EGFR with IC50 of 0.1 μM, 135-fold more selective for EGFR versus ErbB2, also inhibits JAK2 with no activity to Lck, Lyn, Btk, Syk and Src.

Selumetinib (AZD6244) is a potent, highly selective MEK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM, also inhibits ERK1/2 phosphorylation with IC50 of 10 nM, no inhibition to p38α, MKK6, EGFR, ErbB2, ERK2, B-Raf, etc. Phase 1/2.
CI-1040 (PD 184352) is an ATP non-competitive MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM, 100-fold more selective for MEK1/2 than MEK5. Phase 2.
Nilotinib (AMN-107) is a Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 less than 30 nM.

Tandutinib (MLN518, CT53518) is a potent FLT3 antagonist with IC50 of 0.22 μM, also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit, 15 to 20-fold higher potency for FLT3 versus CSF-1R and >100-fold selectivity for the same target versus FGFR, EGFR and KDR. Phase 1/2.
GDC-0941 is a potent inhibitor of PI3Kα/δ with IC50 of 3 nM, with modest selectivity against p110β (11-fold) and p110γ (25-fold).
MK-2206 2HCl is a highly selective inhibitor of Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 8 nM/12 nM/65 nM, respectively; no inhibitory activities against 250 other protein kinases observed. Phase 2.
MLN8054 is a potent and selective inhibitor of Aurora A with IC50 of 4 nM. It is more than 40-fold selective for Aurora A than Aurora B. Phase 1.
TAE684 is a potent and selective ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM, 100-fold more sensitive for ALK than InsR.
XL147 is a selective and reversible class I PI3K inhibitor for PI3Kα/δ/γ with IC50 of 39 nM/36 nM/23 nM, less potent to PI3Kβ. Phase 1/2.

SNS-032 has firstly been described as a selective inhibitor of CDK2 with IC50 of 48 nM and is 10- and 20-fold selective over CDK1/CDK4. It is also found to be sensitive to CDK7/9 with IC50 of 62 nM/4 nM, with little effect on CDK6. Phase 1.

BEZ235 (NVP-BEZ235) is a dual ATP-competitive PI3K and mTOR inhibitor for p110α/γ/δ/β and mTOR(p70S6K) with IC50 of 4 nM/5 nM/7 nM/75 nM/6 nM, respectively. Inhibits ATR with IC50 of 21 nM; shown to be poor inhibitory to Akt and PDK1. Phase 1/2.
Dasatinib is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of ＜1 nM, 0.8 nM and 79 nM, respectively.
NVP-AEW541 is a potent inhibitor of IGF-1R with IC50 of 86 nM, 27-fold greater selectivity for IGF-1R than InsR.
Temsirolimus (CCI-779) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.76 μM.
SL327 is a selective inhibitor for MEK1/2 with IC50 of 0.18 μM/ 0.22 μM, no activity towards Erk1, MKK3, MKK4, c-JUN, PKC, PKA, or CamKII;capable of transport through the blood-brain barrier.
SU11274 is a selective Met inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM, no effects on PGDFRβ, EGFR or Tie2.
Vatalanib (PTK787) is an inhibitor of VEGFR2/KDR with IC50 of 37 nM, less potent against VEGFR1/Flt-1, 18-fold against VEGFR3/Flt-4. Phase 1/2.
BI2536 is a potent Plk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.83 nM. It shows 4- and 11-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and Plk3. Phase 2.

Cabozantinib (XL184, BMS-907351) is a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM, respectively.
AZD1152-HQPA (Barasertib) is a highly selective Aurora B inhibitor with IC50 of 0.37 nM, ~100 fold more selective for Aurora B over Aurora A.
Nintedanib (BIBF 1120) is a potent triple angiokinase inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3, FGFR1/2/3 and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 34 nM/13 nM/13 nM, 69 nM/37 nM/108 nM and 59 nM/65 nM. Phase 3.
Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus) is a selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 nM; while not classified as a prodrug, mTOR inhibition and FKBP12 binding is similar to rapamycin.
Pazopanib (GW786034) is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR, FGFR, c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM, 30 nM, 47 nM, 84 nM, 74 nM, 140 nM and 146 nM, respectively.
Vandetanib (ZD6474) is a potent inhibitor of VEGFR2 with IC50 of 40 nM.
PF-2341066 (Crizotinib) is a potent inhibitor of c-Met and ALK with IC50 of 11 nM and 24 nM, respectivley.
Brivanib is an ATP-competitive inhibitor against VEGFR2 with IC50 of 25 nM, moderate potency against VEGFR-1 and FGFR-1, but >240-fold against PDGFR-β. Phase 3.
U0126-EtOH is a highly selective inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 0.07 μM/0.06 μM, 100-fold higher affinity for ΔN3-S218E/S222D MEK than PD098059.

Foretinib (GSK1363089) is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of HGFR and VEGFR, mostly for Met and KDR with IC50 of 0.4 nM and 0.9 nM. Less potent against Ron, Flt-1/3/4, Kit, PDGFRα/β and Tie-2, and little activity to FGFR1 and EGFR. Phase 2.
Everolimus (RAD001) is an mTOR inhibitor of FKBP12 with IC50 of 1.6-2.4 nM.
PLX4720 is a potent and selective inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 13 nM, equally potent to c-Raf-1(Y340D and Y341D mutations), 10-fold selectivity for B-RafV600E than wild-type B-Raf.

Afatinib (BIBW2992) irreversibly inhibits EGFR/HER2 including EGFR(wt), EGFR(L858R), EGFR(L858R/T790M) and HER2 with IC50 of 0.5 nM, 0.4 nM, 10 nM and 14 nM, respectively; 100-fold more active against Gefitinib-resistant L858R-T790M EGFR mutant. Phase 3.
Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744) is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM, >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl. Phase 3.
PD0325901 (PD325901) is selective and non ATP-competitive MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.33 nM, roughly 500-fold more potent than CI-1040 on phosphorylation of ERK1 and ERK2. Phase 1/2.

VX-680 (Tozasertib, MK-0457) is a pan-Aurora inhibitor, mostly against Aurora A with Kiapp of 0.6 nM, less potent towards Aurora B/Aurora C and 100-fold more selective for Aurora A than 55 other kinases. Phase 2.
PHA-665752 is a potent, selective and ATP-competitive c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 9 nM,  >50-fold selectivity for c-Met than RTKs or STKs.
NVP-ADW742 is an IGF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 0.17 μM, >16-fold more potent against IGF-1R than InsR;  little activity to HER2, PDGFR, VEGFR-2, Bcr-Abl and c-Kit.

ZM 447439 is a selective and ATP-competitive inhibitor for Aurora A and Aurora B with IC50 of 110 nM and 130 nM, respectively. It is more than 8-fold selective for Aurora A/B than MEK1, Src, Lck and has little effect againstCDK1/2/4, Plk1, Chk1, etc.
SGX-523 is a selective Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM, no activity to BRAFV599E, c-Raf, Abl and p38α. Phase 1.

BMS-754807 is a potent and reversible inhibitor of IGF-1R/InsR with IC50 of 1.8 nM/1.7 nM, less potent to Met, Aurora A/B, TrkA/B and Ron, and shows little activity to Flt3, Lck, MK2, PKA, PKC etc. Phase 1/2.
Roscovitine (Seliciclib, CYC202) is a potent and selective CDK inhibitor for Cdc2, CDK2 and CDK5 with IC50 of 0.65 μM, 0.7 μM and 0.16 μM. It shows little effect on CDK4/6. Phase 2.
Bosutinib (SKI-606) is a novel, dual Src/Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM and 1 nM, respectively.
Gefitinib (ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173, Tyr992, Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM, 37nM, 26 nM and 57 nM, respectively.
PI-103 is a multi-targeted PI3K inhibitor for p110α/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 2 nM/3 nM/3 nM/15 nM, less potent to mTOR/DNA-PK with IC50 of 30 nM/23 nM.
Y-27632 2HCl is a selective ROCK1 (p160ROCK) inhibitor with Ki of 140 nM, exhibits >200-fold selectivity over other kinases, including PKC, cAMP-dependent protein kinase, MLCK and PAK.
ZSTK474 inhibits class I PI3Kisoforms with IC50 of 37 nM, mostly PI3Kδ.
OSI-906 (Linsitinib) is a selective inhibitor of IGF-1R with IC50 of 35 nM; modestly potent to InsR with IC50 of 75 nM, and no activity towards Abl, ALK, BTK, EGFR, FGFR1/2, PKA etc. Phase 3.
GDC-0879 is a novel, potent, and selective B-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 0.13 nM with activity against c-Raf as well; no inhibition known to other protein kinases.
GSK690693 is a pan-Akt inhibitor targeting Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/13 nM/9 nM, also sensitive to the AGC kinase family: PKA, PrkX and PKC isozymes. Phase 1.
Alisertib (MLN8237) is a selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM. It has >200-fold higher selectivity for Aurora A than Aurora B. Phase 3.

SNS-314 Mesylate is a potent and selective inhibitor of Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 9 nM, 31 nM, and 3 nM, respectively. It is less potent to Trk A/B, Flt4, Fms, Axl, c-Raf and DDR2. Phase 1.

E7080 (Lenvatinib) is a multi-target inhibitor, mostly for VEGFR2(KDR)/VEGFR3(Flt-4) with IC50 of 4 nM/5.2 nM, less potent against VEGFR1/Flt-1, ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR2/3 against FGFR1, PDGFRα/β. Phase 3.
WZ8040 is a novel mutant-selective irreversible EGFRT790M inhibitor, does not inhibit ERBB2 phosphorylation (T798I).

AG-1024 (Tyrphostin) inhibits IGF-1R autophosphorylation with IC50 of 7 μM, is less potent to IR with IC50 of 57 μM and specifically distinguishes between InsR and IGF-1R (as compared to other tyrphostins).
Zoledronic acid induces apoptosis in osteoclasts by inhibiting enzymes of the mevalonate pathway and preventing the isoprenylation of small GTP-binding proteins such as Ras and Rho.
Pelitinib (EKB-569) is a potent irreversible EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 38.5 nM. Phase2.
GSK429286A is a selective inhibitor of ROCK1 and ROCK2 with IC50 of 14 nM and 63 nM, respectively.
CCT129202 is an ATP-competitive pan-Aurora inhibitor for Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 0.042 μM, 0.198 μM and 0.227 μM, respectively. It is less potent to FGFR3, GSK3β, PDGFRβ, etc.
R406 (free base) is a potent Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 2.
KU-60019 is an improved analogue of KU-55933, with IC50 of 6.3 nM for ATM, 270- and 1600-fold more selective for ATM than DNA-PK and ATR,and is a highly effective radiosensitizer.
PF-573228 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 4 nM, ~50- to 250-fold selective for FAK than Pyk2, CDK1/7 and GSK-3β.
CP-724,714 is a potent, selective inhibitor of HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 10 nM, >640-fold selectivity against EGFR, InsR, IRG-1R, PDGFR, VEGFR2, Abl, Src, c-Met etc. Phase 2.

ENMD-2076 has selective activity against Aurora A and Flt3 with IC50 of 14 nM and 1.86 nM, 25-fold selective for Aurora A than over Aurora B and less potent to VEGFR2/KDR and VEGFR3, FGFR1 and FGFR2 and PDGFRα. Phase 2.
Amuvatinib (MP-470) is a potent and multi-targeted inhibitor of c-Kit, PDGFRα and Flt3 with IC50 of 10 nM, 40 nM and 81 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

Genistein, a phytoestrogen found in soy products, is a highly specific inhibitor of protein tyrosine kinase (PTK)  which blocks the mitogenic effect mediated by EGF on NIH-3T3 cells with IC50 of 12μM or by insulin with IC50 of 19 μM.
Aurora A Inhibitor I is a novel, potent, and selective inhibitor of Aurora A with IC50 of 3.4 nM. It is 1000-fold more selective for Aurora A than Aurora B.
AS-703026 is a highly selective, potent, ATP non-competitive allosteric inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 5 nM-2 μM in MM cell lines. Phase 1/2.
SAR245409 (XL765) is a dual inhibitor of mTOR/PI3K, mostly for p110γ with IC50 of 9 nM; also inhibits DNA-PK and mTOR. Phase 1/2.
CP 673451 is a selective inhibitor of PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 10 nM/1 nM, exhibits >450-fold selectivity over other angiogenic receptors, has antiangiogenic and antitumor activity.
BS-181 is a highly selective CDK7 inhibitor with IC50 of 21 nM. It is more than 40-fold selective for CDK7 than CDK1, 2, 4, 5, 6, or 9.
BMS-265246 is a potent and selective CDK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM/9 nM. It is 25-fold more selective for CDK1/2 than CDK4.
TGX-221 is a p110β-specific inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, 1000-fold more selective for p110β than p110α.
CUDC-101 is a potent multi-targeted inhibitor against HDAC, EGFR and HER2 with IC50 of 4.4 nM, 2.4 nM, and 15.7 nM, and inhibits class I/II HDACs, but not class III, Sir-type HDACs. Phase 1.

JNJ-7706621 is pan-CDK inhibitor with the highest potency on CDK1/2 with IC50 of 9 nM/4 nM and showing >6-fold selectivity for CDK1/2 than CDK3/4/6. It also potently inhibits Aurora A/B and has no activity on Plk1 and Wee1.
TG100115 is a PI3Kγ/δ inhibitor with IC50 of 83 nM/235 nM, with little effect on PI3Kα/β. Phase 1/2.

PHA-680632 is potent inhibitor of Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 27 nM, 135 nM and 120 nM, respectively. It has 10- to 200-fold higher IC50 for FGFR1, FLT3, LCK, PLK1, STLK2, and VEGFR2/3.
HMN-214 is a prodrug of HMN-176, which alters the cellular spatial orientation of Plk1.
AT7519 is a multi-CDK inhibitor for CDK1, 2, 4, 6 and 9 with IC50 of 10-210 nM. It is less potent to CDK3 and little active to CDK7. Phase 1.
AZD8055 is a novel ATP-competitive mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.8 nM with excellent selectivity (∼1,000-fold) against PI3K isoforms and ATM/DNA-PK. Phase 1.
Fasudil (HA-1077) is a potent inhibitor of ROCK-II, PKA,  PKG,  PKC, and MLCK with Ki of 0.33 μM, 1.6 μM, 1.6 μM, 3.3 μM and 36 μM, respectively.
AZD8330 is a novel, selective, non-ATP competitive MEK 1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 7 nM. Phase 1.
WZ3146 is a mutant-selective irreversible inhibitor of EGFR(L858R) and EGFR(E746_A750) with IC50 of 2 nM and 2 nM; does not inhibit ERBB2 phosphorylation (T798I).
PIK-75 is a p110α inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM (200-fold more potently than p110β), isoform-specific mutants at Ser773, and also potently inhibits DNA-PK with IC50 of 2 nM.
PD173074 is a potent FGFR1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~25 nM and also inhibits VEGFR2 with IC50 of 100-200 nM, ~1000-fold selective for FGFR1 than PDGFR and c-Src.
GSK1059615 is a dual inhibitor of PI3Kα/β/δ/γ (reversible) and mTOR with IC50 of 0.4 nM/0.6 nM/2 nM/5 nM and 12 nM, respectively. Phase 1.
VX-745 is a potent and selective inhibitor of p38α with IC50 of 10 nM, 22-fold greater selectivity versus p38β and no inhibition to p38γ.
AEE788 is a potent inhibitor of EGFR and HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 2 nM and 6 nM, less potent to VEGFR2/KDR, c-Abl, c-Src, and Flt-1, does not inhibit Ins-R, IGF-1R, PKCα and CDK1. Phase 1/2.
Quizartinib (AC220) is a second-generation FLT3 inhibitor for Flt3(ITD/WT) with IC50 of 1.1 nM/4.2 nM, 10-fold more selective for Flt3 than KIT, PDGFRα, PDGFRβ, RET, and CSF-1R. Phase 1/2.
PHT-427 is a dual Akt and PDPK1 inhibitor (high affinity binding for the PH domains of Akt and PDPK1) with Ki of 2.7 μM and 5.2 μM, respectively.

BIRB 796 (Doramapimod) is a highly selective p38α MAPK inhibitor with Kd of 0.1 nM, 330-fold greater selectivity versus JNK2, weak inhibition for c-RAF, Fyn and Lck, insignificant inhibition of ERK-1, SYK, IKK2, ZAP-70, EGFR, HER2, PKA, PKC, PKCα/β/γ.

Neratinib (HKI-272) is a highly selective HER2 and EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 59 nM and 92 nM; weakly inhibits KDR and Src, no significant inhibition to Akt, CDK1/2/4, IKK-2, MK-2, PDK1, c-Raf and c-Met. Phase 3.

CYC116 is a potent inhibitor of Aurora A/B with Ki of 8.0 nM/9.2 nM, is less potent to VEGFR2 (Ki of 44 nM), with 50-fold greater potency than CDKs, not active against PKA, Akt/PKB, PKC, no effect on GSK-3α/β, CK2, Plk1 and SAPK2A. Phase 1.

Tivozanib (AV-951) is a potent and selective VEGFR inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 30 nM/6.5 nM/15 nM, and also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit, low activity observed against FGFR-1, Flt3, c-Met EGFR and IGF-1R. Phase 3.

WYE-354 is a potent, specific and ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with IC50 of 5 nM, blocks mTORC1/P-S6K(T389) and mTORC2/P-AKT(S473) not P-AKT(T308), selective for mTOR than PI3Kα (>100-fold) and PI3Kγ (>500-fold).
MGCD-265 is a potent, multi-target and ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met and VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 1 nM, 3 nM/3 nM/4 nM, respectively; also inhibits Ron and Tie2. Phase 1/2.
Thiazovivin (Tzv) is a novel ROCK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 μM, promotes hESC survival after single-cell dissociation.
PHA-793887 is a novel and potent inhibitor of CDK2, CDK5 and CDK7 with IC50 of 8 nM, 5 nM and 10 nM. It is greater than 6-fold more selective for CDK2, 5, and 7 than CDK1, 4, and 9. Phase 1.
Hesperadin potently inhibits Aurora B with IC50 of 250 nM. It markedly reduces the activity of AMPK, Lck, MKK1, MAPKAP-K1, CHK1 and PHK while it does not inhibit MKK1 activity in vivo.
KRN 633 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 170 nM/160 nM/125 nM, weakly inhibits PDGFR-α/β and c-Kit, does not block the phosphorylation of FGFR-1, EGFR or c-Met in cell.
Tie2 kinase inhibitor is an optimized compound of SB-203580, selective to Tie2 with IC50 of 0.25 μM, 200-fold more potent than p38.
KW-2449 is a multiple-targeted inhibitor, mostly for Flt3 with IC50 of 6.6 nM, modestly potent to FGFR1, Bcr-Abl and Aurora A; little effect on PDGFRβ, IGF-1R, EGFR. Phase 1.
WZ4002 is a novel, mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor for EGFR(L858R)/(T790M) with IC50 of 2 nM/8 nM; does not inhibit ERBB2 phosphorylation (T798I).
YM201636 is a selective PIKfyve inhibitor with IC50 of 33 nM, less potent to p110α and insensitive to Fabl (yeast orthologue).
Vemurafenib (PLX4032, RG7204) is a novel and potent inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 31 nM.
Rigosertib (ON-01910) is a non-ATP-competitive inhibitor of PLK1 with IC50 of 9 nM. It shows 30-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and no activity to Plk3. Phase 3.

SP600125 is a broad-spectrum JNK inhibitor for JNK1, JNK2 and JNK3 with IC50 of 40 nM, 40 nM and 90 nM, respectively; 10-fold greater selectivity against MKK4, 25-fold greater selectivity against MKK3, MKK6, PKB, and PKCα, and 100-fold selectivity against ERK2, p38, Chk1, EGFR etc.
PIK-93 is the first potent, synthetic PI4K (PI4KIIIβ) inhibitor with IC50 of 19 nM; shown to inhibit PI3Kα with IC50 of 39 nM.
BIX02188 is a selective inhibitor of MEK5 with IC50 of 4.3 nM, also inhibits ERK5 catalytic activity with IC50 of 810 nM, and does not inhibit closely related kinases MEK1, MEK2, ERK2, and JNK2.
AT7867 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of Akt1/2/3 and p70S6K/PKA with IC50 of 32 nM/17 nM/47 nM and 85 nM/20 nM, respectively; little activity outside the AGC kinase family.
H 89 2HCl is a potent PKA inhibitor with Ki of 48 nM, 10-fold selective for PKA than PKG, greater than 500-fold selectivity than PKC, MLCK, calmodulin kinase II and casein kinase I/II.
RAF265 (CHIR-265) is a potent selective inhibitor of C-Raf/B-Raf/B-Raf V600E with IC50 of 3-60 nM, and exhibits potent inhibition on VEGFR2 phosphorylation with EC50 of 30 nM. Phase 2.
PD98059 is a non-ATP competitive MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 2 μM, specifically inhibits MEK-1-mediated activation of MAPK; does not directly inhibit ERK1 or ERK2.
OSI-930 is a potent inhibitor of Kit, KDR and CSF-1R with IC50 of 80 nM, 9 nM and 15 nM, respectively; also potent to Flt-1, c-Raf and Lck and low activity against PDGFRα/β, Flt-3 and Abl. Phase 1.

BX795 is a potent and specific PDK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM, 140- and 1600-fold more selective for PDK1 than PKA and PKC, respectively. Meanwhile, in comparison to GSK3β more than 100-fold selectivity observed for PDK1.
Ki8751 is a potent and selective inhibitor of VEGFR2 with IC50 of 0.9 nM, >40-fold selective for VEGFR2 than c-Kit, PDGFRα and FGFR-2, little activity to EGFR, HGFR and InsR.
AZD6482 is a PI3Kβ inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM, 8-, 87- and 109-fold more selective to PI3Kβ than PI3Kδ, PI3Kα and PI3Kγ. Phase 1.
Ponatinib (AP24534) is a novel, potent multi-target inhibitor of Abl, PDGFRα, VEGFR2, FGFR1 and Src with IC50 of 0.37 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.5 nM, 2.2 nM and 5.4 nM, respectively.
BIX02189 is a selective inhibitor of MEK5 with IC50 of 1.5 nM, also inhibits ERK5 catalytic activity with IC50 of 810 nM, and does not inhibit closely related kinases MEK1, MEK2, ERK2, and JNK2.

BMS-777607 is a Met-related inhibitor for c-Met, Axl, Ron and Tyro3 with IC50 of 3.9 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.8 nM and 4.3 nM, 40-fold more selective for Met-related targets versus Lck, VEGFR-2, and TrkA/B, and more than 500-fold greater selectivity versus all other receptor and non receptor kinases. Phase 1/2.
TWS119 is a GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 30 nM; capable of inducing neuronal differentiation and may be useful to stem cell biology.

PF-4708671 is a cell-permeable inhibitor of p70 ribosomal S6 kinase (S6K1 isoform) with Ki/IC50 of 20 nM/160 nM, 400-fold greater selectivity for S6K1 than S6K2, and 4- and >20-fold selectivity for S6K1 than MSK1 and RSK1/2, respectively. First S6K1-specific inhibitor to be reported.
Regorafenib (BAY 73-4506) is a multi-target inhibitor for VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ, Kit, RET and Raf-1 with IC50 of 13 nM/4.2 nM/46 nM, 22 nM, 7 nM, 1.5 nM and 2.5 nM, respectively.
KU-0063794 is a potent and highly specific dual-mTOR inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of ~10 nM; no effect on PI3Ks.

BX912 is a potent and specific PDK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 12 nM, 9- and 105- fold greater selectivity for PDK1 than PKA and PKC, respectively. In comparison to GSK3β, selectivity for PDK1 is 600-fold.
INCB018424 is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3. Phase 3.

SU6668 has greatest potency against PDGFR autophosphorylation with Ki of 8 nM, but also strongly inhibits Flk-1 and FGFR1 trans-phosphorylation, little activity against IGF-1R, Met, Src, Lck, Zap70, Abl and CDK2; does not inhibit EGFR. Phase 3.
LY2228820 is a novel and potent inhibitor of p38 MAPK with IC50 of 7 nM, does not alter p38 MAPK activation. Phase 1/2.
AZD7762 is a potent and selective inhibitor of Chk1 with IC50 of 5 nM. It is equally potent against Chk2 and less potent against CAM, Yes, Fyn, Lyn, Hck and Lck. Phase 1.
PD318088 is a non-ATP competitive allosteric MEK1/2 inhibitor, binds simultaneously with ATP in a region of the MEK1 active site that is adjacent to the ATP-binding site.
Acadesine results in accumulation of ZMP, which mimics the stimulating effect of AMP on AMPK and AMPK kinase. Phase 3.
LY2784544 is a potent JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM, effective in JAK2V617F, 8- and 20-fold selective versus JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 2.

BGJ398 (NVP-BGJ398) is a potent and selective FGFR inhibitor for FGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 0.9 nM/1.4 nM/1 nM, >40-fold selective for FGFR versus FGFR4 and VEGFR2, and little activity to Abl, Fyn, Kit, Lck, Lyn and Yes. Phase 2.
OSI-420 is the active metabolite of Erlotinib (EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM).

CAL-101 (Idelalisib, GS-1101) is a selective p110δ inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 nM; shown to have 40- to 300-fold greater selectivity for p110δ thanp110α/β/γ, and 400- to 4000-fold more selectivity to p110δ than C2β, hVPS34, DNA-PK and mTOR. Phase 3.
Honokiol is the active principle of magnolia extract that inhibits Akt-phosphorylation and promotes ERK1/2phosphorylation. Phase 3.
PP-121 is a multi-targeted inhibitor of PDGFR, Hck, mTOR, VEGFR2, Src and Abl with IC50 of 2 nM, 8 nM, 10 nM, 12 nM, 14 nM and 18 nM, also inhibits DNA-PK with IC50 of 60 nM.
NU7441 is a highly potent and selective DNA-PK inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM and also inhibits PI3K with IC50 of 5 μM.
Ibrutinib is a potent and highly selective Btk inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 nM, modestly potent to Bmx, CSK, FGR, BRK, HCK, less potent to EGFR, Yes, ErbB2, JAK3, etc.

GDC-0980 (RG7422) is a potent, class I PI3K inhibitor for PI3Kα/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 5 nM/27 nM/7 nM/14 nM, respectively. Also a mTOR inhibitor with Ki of 17 nM, and highly selective versus others PIKK family kinases. Phase 2.
PH-797804 is a novel pyridinone inhibitor of p38α with IC50 of 26 nM; 4-fold more selective versus p38β and does not inhibit JNK2. Phase 2.

PHA-767491 is a potent ATP-competitive dual Cdc7/CDK9 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM and 34 nM, respectively.It displays ~20-fold selectivity against CDK1/2 and GSK3-β, 50-fold selectivity against MK2 and CDK5, 100-fold selectivity against PLK1 and CHK2.

AST-1306 is a novel irreversible inhibitor of EGFR and ErbB2 with IC50 of 0.5 nM and 3 nM, also effective in mutation EGFR T790M/L858R, more potent to ErbB2-overexpressing cells, 3000-fold selective for ErbB family than other kinases,
PIK-293 is a PI3K inhibitor, mostly for PI3Kδ with IC50 of 0.24 μM, 500-, 100- and 50-fold less potent to PI3Kα/β/γ, respectively.
PIK-294 is a highly selective p110δ inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM, 1000-, 49- and 16-fold less potent to PI3Kα/β/γ, respectively.
Indirubin is a potent cyclin-dependent kinases and GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of about 5 μM and 0.6 μM.
OSI-027 is a selective and potent dual inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of 22 nM and 65 nM, and more than 100-fold selectivity observed for mTOR than PI3Kα, PI3Kβ, PI3Kγ or DNA-PK.
GSK2126458 is a highly selective and potent inhibitor of p110α/β/δ/γ, mTORC1/2 with Ki of 0.019 nM/0.13 nM/0.024 nM/0.06 nM and 0.18 nM/0.3 nM, respectively. Phase 1.
AS-604850 is a selective, ATP-competitive PI3Kγ inhibitor with IC50 of 250 nM, over 80-fold selectivity for PI3Kγ than PI3Kδ/β, and 18-fold more selective for PI3Kγ than PI3Kα.
A-769662 is a potent, reversible AMPK activator with EC50of 0.8 μM, little effect on GPPase/FBPase activity.

PF-299804 is a potent, irreversible pan-ErbB inhibitor, mostly to EGFR with IC50 of 6 nM, effective against NSCLCs with EGFR or ERBB2 mutations (resistant to gefitinib) as well as those harboring the EGFR T790M mutation. Phase 2.

PF-04691502 is an ATP-competitive PI3K(α/β/δ/γ)/mTOR dual inhibitor with Ki of 1.8 nM/2.1 nM/1.6 nM/1.9 nM and 16 nM, little activity against either Vps34, AKT, PDK1, p70S6K, MEK, ERK, p38, or JNK. Phase 2.

AZD8931 is a reversible, ATP competitive inhibitor of EGFR, ErbB2 and ErbB3 with IC50 of 4 nM, 3 nM and 4 nM, more potent than Gefitinib or Lapatinib against NSCLC cell, 100-fold more selective for the ErbB family than MNK1 and Flt. Phase 1/2.
AZ 960 is a novel ATP competitive JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of <3 nM and 0.45 nM, 3-fold selectivity of AZ960 for JAK2 over JAK3.
Telatinib is a potent inhibitor of VEGFR2/3, c-Kit and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 6 nM/4 nM, 1 nM and 15 nM, respectively. Phase 2.
Quercetin is a natural flavonoid present in vegetables, fruit and wine and is a PI3K inhibitor with IC50 of 2.4 – 5.4 μM.
Fostamatinib (R788), a prodrug of the active metabolite R406, is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 2.
WYE-125132 is a highly potent, ATP-competitive mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.19 nM; highly selective for mTOR versus PI3Ks or PI3K-related kinases hSMG1 and ATR.
CAY10505 is dehydroxyl of AS-252424, which is a PI3Kγ inhibitor with IC50 of 33 nM.
CH5132799 inhibits class I PI3Ks, particularly PI3Kα with IC50 of 14 nM; less potent to PI3Kβδγ, while sensitive in PIK3CA mutations cell lines. Phase 1.
AG-1478 (Tyrphostin AG-1478) is a selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM, almost no activity on HER2-Neu, PDGFR, Trk, Bcr-Abl and InsR.
CCT137690 is a highly selective inhibitor of Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 15 nM, 25 nM and 19 nM. It has little effect on hERG ion-channel.
GSK461364 inhibits purified Plk1 with Ki of 2.2 nM. It is more than 1000-fold selective against Plk2/3. Phase 1.
Mubritinib (TAK-165) is a potent inhibitor of HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 6 nM; no activity to EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, JAK1, Src and Blk.
BI6727 (Volasertib) is a highly potent Plk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.87 nM. It shows 6- and 65-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and Plk3. Phase 2.
Chrysophanic acid (Chrysophanol), a natural anthraquinone isolated from Dianella longifolia, is a EGFR/mTOR pathway inhibitor.
LY2603618 is a selective Chk1 inhibitor with potential anti-tumor activity.
A-674563 is an Akt1 inhibitor with Ki of 11 nM, modest potent to PKA and >30-fold selective for Akt1 over PKC.
CHIR-124 is a novel and potent Chk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3 nM. It shows 2,000-fold selectivity against Chk2, 500- to 5,000-fold less activity against CDK2/4 and Cdc2.
KX2-391 (KX01), the first clinical Src inhibitor (peptidomimetic class) that targets the peptide substrate site of Src, with GI50 of 9-60 nM in cancer cell lines. Phase 1/2.
SB415286 is a potent GSK3α inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 78 nM/31 nM with equally effective inhibition of GSK-3β.
CHIR-98014 is a potent GSK-3α/β inhibitor with IC50 of 0.65 nM/0.58 nM, with the ability to distinguish GSK-3 from its closest homologs Cdc2 and ERK2.
R406 is a potent Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 2.
PP242 is a selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 8 nM; targets both mTOR complexes with >10- and 100-fold selectivity for mTOR than PI3Kδ or PI3Kα/β/γ, respectively.
Palomid 529 inhibits both the mTORC1 and mTORC2 complexes, reduces phosphorylation of pAktS473, pGSK3βS9, and pS6 but no effect observed on pMAPK or pAktT308. Phase 1.
Imatinib is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM, respectively.
PKI-587 is a highly potent dual inhibitor of PI3Kα, PI3Kγ and mTOR with IC50 of 0.4 nM, 5.4 nM and 1.6 nM, respectively. Phase 2.
AS-252424 is a novel, potent PI3Kγ inhibitor with IC50 of 30 nM with 30-fold selectivity for PI3Kγ than PI3Kα, and low inhibitory activity towards PI3Kδ/β.
NVP-BSK805 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 nM,>20-fold selectivity towards JAK1, JAK3 and TYK2.
GSK1838705A is a potent IGF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 2.0 nM, modestly potent to IR and ALK with IC50 of 1.6 nM and 0.5 nM, respectively, and little activity to other protein kinases.

Crenolanib (CP-868596) is a potent and selective inhibitor of PDGFRα/β with Kd of 2.1 nM/3.2 nM, also potently inhibits FLT3, sensitive to D842V mutation not V561D mutation, >100-fold more selective for PDGFR than c-Kit, VEGFR-2, TIE-2, FGFR-2, EGFR, erbB2, and Src.
AZ628 is a new pan-Raf inhibitor for BRAF, BRAFV600E, and c-Raf-1 with IC50 of 105 nM, 34 nM and 29 nM, also inhibits VEGFR2, DDR2, Lyn, Flt1, FMS, etc.
SGI-1776 is a novel ATP competitive inhibitor of Pim1 with IC50 of 7 nM, 50- and 10-fold selective versus Pim2 and Pim3, also potent to Flt3 and haspin. Phase 1.
CYT387 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of JAK1/JAK2 with IC50 of 11 nM/18 nM, ~10-fold selectivity versus JAK3. Phase 1/2.

WP1130 (Degrasyn) is a selective deubiquitinase (DUB: USP5, UCH-L1, USP9x, USP14, and UCH37) inhibitor and also suppresses Bcr/Abl, also a JAK2 transducer (without affecting 20S proteasome) and activator of transcription (STAT).
Phenformin hydrochloride is a hydrochloride salt of phenformin that is an anti-diabetic drug from the biguanide class.

DCC-2036 is a conformational control Bcr-Abl inhibitor for Abl1(WT) and Abl1(T315I) with IC50 of 0.8 nM and 4 nM, also inhibits SRC, LYN, FGR, HCK, KDR, FLT3, and Tie-2, and low activity to seen towards c-Kit. Phase 1/2.

PF-00562271 is the benzenesulfonate salt of PF-562271, which is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs. Phase 1.
R547 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of CDK1/2/4 with Ki of 2 nM/3 nM/1 nM. It is less potent to CDK7 and GSK3α/β, while inactive to other kinases.
TAK-901 is a novel inhibitor of Aurora A/B with IC50 of 21 nM/15 nM. It is not a potent inhibitor of cellular JAK2, c-Src or Abl. Phase 1.
SCH 900776 is a selective Chk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM. It shows 500-fold selectivity against Chk2. Phase 2.
AMG 458 is a potent c-Met inhibitor with Ki of 1.2 nM, ~350-fold selectivity for c-Met than VEGFR2 in cells.
BMS-794833 is a potent ATP competitive inhibitor of Met/VEGFR2 with IC50 of 1.7 nM/15 nM, also inhibits Ron, Axl and Flt3 with IC50 of <3 nM; a prodrug of BMS-817378. Phase 1.
SB590885 is a potent B-Raf inhibitor with Ki of 0.16 nM, 11-fold greater selectivity for B-Raf over c-Raf, no inhibition to other human kinases.
BKM120 is a selective PI3K inhibitor of p110α/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 52 nM/166 nM/116 nM/262 nM, respectively. Reduced potency against VPS34, mTOR, DNAPK, with little activity to PI4Kβ. Phase 1/2.
TAK-733 is a potent and selective MEK allosteric site inhibitor for MEK1 with IC50 of 3.2 nM, inactive to Abl1, AKT3, c-RAF, CamK1, CDK2, c-Met, etc. Phase 1.
CCT128930 is a potent, ATP-competitive and selective inhibitor of Akt2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 28-fold greater selectivity for Akt2 than the closely related PKA kinase.
Trametinib (GSK1120212) is a highly specific and potent MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.92 nM/1.8 nM, no inhibition of the kinase activities of c-Raf, B-Raf, ERK1/2. Phase 3.

WAY-600 is a potent, ATP-competitive and selective inhibitor of mTOR with IC50 of 9 nM; blocks mTORC1/P-S6K(T389) and mTORC2/P-AKT(S473) but not P-AKT(T308); selective for mTOR than PI3Kα (>100-fold) and PI3Kγ (>500-fold).

AMG 900 is a potent and highly selective pan-Aurora kinases inhibitor for Aurora A/B/C with IC50 of 5 nM/4 nM /1 nM. It is >10-fold selective for Aurora kinases than p38α, Tyk2, JNK2, Met and Tie2. Phase 1.
TG-101348 (SAR302503) is a selective inhibitor of JAK2 with IC50 of 3 nM, 35- and 334-fold more selective for JAK2 versus JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 1/2.
NVP-BGT226 is a novel class I PI3K/mTOR inhibitor for PI3Kα/β/γ with IC50 of 4 nM/63 nM/38 nM. Phase 1/2.

NVP-BHG712 is a specific EphB4 inhibitor with ED50 of 25 nM that discriminates between VEGFR and EphB4 inhibition; also shows activity against c-Raf, c-Src and c-Abl with IC50 of 0.395 μM, 1.266 μM and 1.667 μM, respectively.
Apatinib is an orally bioavailable, selective VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM.
Asiatic acid is the aglycone of asiaticoside isolated from the plant Centella asiatica, commonly used in wound healing.
AZD5438 is a potent inhibitor of CDK1/2/9 with IC50 of 16 nM/6 nM/20 nM. It is less potent to CDK5/6 and also inhibits GSK3β. Phase 1.
A66 is a potent and specific p110α inhibitor with IC50 of 32 nM, >100 fold selectivity for p110α over other class-I PI3K isoforms.

Flavopiridol competes with ATP to inhibit CDKs including CDK1, CDK2, CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of ~ 40 nM. It is 7.5-fold more selective for CDK1/2/4/6 than CDK7. Flavopiridol is initially found to inhibit EGFR and PKA. Phase 1/2.

TG101209 is a selective JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM, less potent to Flt3 and RET with IC50 of 25 nM and 17 nM, ~30-fold selective for JAK2 than JAK3, sensitive to JAK2V617F and MPLW515L/K mutations.
ZM 336372 is a potent and selective c-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 70 nM, 10-fold selectivity over B-RAF, no inhibition to PKA/B/C, AMPK, p70S6, etc.
GSK1070916 is a reversible and ATP-competitive inhibitor of Aurora B/C with IC50 of 3.5 nM/6.5 nM. It displays >100-fold selectivity against the closely related Aurora A-TPX2 complex. Phase 1.
PHA-848125 is a potent, ATP-competitive CDK inhibitor for CDK2 with IC50 of 45 nM. It is >3-fold more selective for CDK2 than CDK1, 2, 4, 5, and 7. Phase 2.
ARRY-380 is a potent and selective HER2 inhibitor with IC50 of 8 nM, equipotent against truncated p95-HER2, 500-fold more selective for HER2 versus EGFR. Phase 1.

Dovitinib Dilactic acid (TKI258 Dilactic acid) is the Dilactic acid of Dovitinib, which is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGFR1 and HER2. Phase 4.
WP1066 is a novel inhibitor of JAK2 and STAT3 with IC50 of 2.30 μM and 2.43 μM in HEL cells; shows activity to JAK2, STAT3, STAT5, and ERK1/2 not JAK1 and JAK3.

Torin 2 is a potent and selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.25 nM; 800-fold greater selectivity for mTOR than PI3K and improved pharmacokinetic properties. Inhibition of ATM/ATR/DNA-PK with EC50 of 28 nM/35 nM/118 nM, respectively.
Golvatinib (E7050) is a dual c-Met and VEGFR-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM and 16 nM, does not inhibit bFGF-stimulated HUVEC growth (up to 1000 nM). Phase 1/2.
Tyrphostin 9 is firstly designed as an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 460 μM, but is also found to be more potent to PDGFR with IC50 of 0.5 μM.
Icotinib is a potent and specific EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, including the EGFR, EGFR(L858R), EGFR(L861Q), EGFR(T790M) and EGFR(T790M, L858R). Phase 4.
VX-702 is a highly selective inhibitor of p38α MAPK, 14-fold higher potency against the p38α versus p38β. Phase 2.
PD168393 is an irreversible EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.70 nM, irreversibly alkylate Cys-773; inactive against insulin, PDGFR, FGFR and PKC.
NU6027 is a potent ATR/CDK inhibitor, inhibits CDK1/2, ATR and DNA-PK with Ki of 2.5 μM/1.3 μM, 0.4 μM and 2.2 μM, enter cells more readily than the 6-aminopurine-based inhibitors.
ARRY334543 is a selective and potent ErbB1(EGFR) and ErbB2(HER2) inhibitor with IC50 of 7 nM and 2 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

MK-5108 (VX-689) is a highly selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 0.064 nM and is 220- and 190-fold more selective for Aurora A than Aurora B/C, while it inhibits TrkA with less than 100-fold selectivity. Phase 1.

AZD4547 is a novel selective FGFR inhibitor targeting FGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 0.2 nM/2.5 nM/1.8 nM, weaker activity against FGFR4, VEGFR2(KDR), and little activity observed against IGFR, CDK2, and p38. Phase 1/2.
NVP-TAE226 is a potent FAK inhibitor with IC50 of 5.5 nM and modestly potent to Pyk2, ~10- to 100-fold less potent against InsR, IGF-1R, ALK, and c-Met.
IMD-0354 is an IKKβ inhibitor and blocks IκBα phosphorylation in NF-κB pathway.
ZM 323881 is a potent and selective VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of <2 nM, almost no activity on VEGFR1, PDGFRβ, FGFR1, EGFR and ErbB2.
CHIR-99021 HCl (CT99021) is hydrochloride of CHIR-99021, which is a GSK-3α/β inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM/6.7 nM; ability to distinguish between GSK-3 and its closest homologs Cdc2 and ERK2.
AP26113 is a potent ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.62 nM, demonstrated ability overcome Crizotinib resistance mediated by a L1196M mutation. Phase 1/2.
AZ20 is a novel potent and selective inhibitor of ATR kinase with IC50 of 5 nM, 8-fold selectivity over mTOR.
TIC10 inactivates Akt and ERK to induce TRAIL through Foxo3a, possesses superior drug properties: delivery across the blood-brain barrier, superior stability and improved pharmacokinetics.

Wortmannin is a PI3K with IC50 of 3 nM, first described PI3K inhibitors, but little selectivity within the PI3K family. Also blocks autophagosome formation and potently inhibits DNA-PK/ATM with IC50 of 16 nM and 150 nM. Phase 4.

MK-2461 is a potent, multi-targeted inhibitor for c-Met(WT/mutants) with IC50 of 0.4-2.5 nM, less potent to Ron, Flt1; 8- to 30-fold greater selectivity of c-Met targets versus FGFR1, FGFR2, FGFR3, PDGFRβ, KDR, Flt3, Flt4, TrkA, and TrkB. Phase 1/2.
.
CEP33779 is a selective JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 nM, >40- and >800-fold versus JAK1 and TYK2.
Tideglusib is an irreversible, non ATP-competitive GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM; fails to inhibit kinases with a Cys homologous to Cys-199 located in the active site. Phase 1/2.
WHI-P154 is a potent JAK3 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 μM, no activity against JAK1 or JAK2, also inhibits EGFR, Src, Abl, VEGFR and MAPK, prevents Stat3, but not Stat5 phosphorylation.
ZM 306416 is a VEGFR (Flt and KDR) inhibitor for VEGFR1 with IC50 of 0.33 μM, but also found to inhibit EGFR with IC50 of <10 nM.
TAK-715 is a p38 MAPK inhibitor for p38α with IC50 of 7.1 nM, 28-fold more selective for p38α over p38β, no inhibition to p38γ/δ, JNK1, ERK1, IKKβ, MEKK1 or TAK1. Phase 2.
ARRY-438162 is a potent inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 12 nM.
PP1 is a potent and selective Src inhibitor for Lck/Fyn with IC50 of 5 nM/ 6 nM.
CGK 733 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ATM/ATR with IC50 of ~200 nM.
CUDC-907 is a dual PI3K and HDAC inhibitor for PI3Kα and HDAC1/2/3/10 with IC50 of 19 nM and 1.7 nM/5 nM/1.8 nM/2.8 nM, respectively. Phase 1.
AZD2014 is a novel mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 2.8 nM; highly selective against multiple PI3K isoforms (α/β/γ/δ). Phase 2.
Dabrafenib (GSK2118436) is a mutant BRAFV600 specific inhibitor with IC50 of 0.8 nM, with 4- and 6-fold less potency against B-Raf(wt) and c-Raf, respectively. Phase 3.
TPCA-1 is an inhibitor of IKK-2 with IC50 of 17.9 nM, inhibits NF-κB pathway, exhibits 22-fold selectivity over IKK-1.
TG100713 is a pan-PI3K inhibitor against PI3Kγ, PI3Kδ, PI3Kα and PI3Kβ with IC50 of 50 nM, 24 nM, 165 nM and 215 nM, respectively.
GNF-2 is a highly selective non-ATP competitive inhibitor of Bcr-Abl, shows no activity to Flt3-ITD, Tel-PDGFR, TPR-MET and Tel-JAK1 transformed tumor cells.
Pazopanib is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR, FGFR, c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM, 30 nM, 47 nM, 84 nM, 74 nM, 140 nM and 146 nM, respectively.
PP2 is Src family kinase inhibitor, potently inhibits Lck/Fyn with IC50 of 4 nM/5 nM, ~100-fold less potent to EGFR, inactive for ZAP-70, JAK2 and PKA.
MK-8745 is a potent and selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 0.6 nM, more than 450-fold selectivity for Aurora A over Aurora B.

AZD1080 is a selective, orally active, brain permeable GSK3 inhibitor, inhibits human GSK3α and GSK3β with Ki of 6.9 nM and 31 nM, respectively, shows >14-fold selectivity against CDK2, CDK5, CDK1 and Erk2.
NVP-BVU972 is a selective and potent Met inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM.
TAK-285 is a novel dual HER2 and EGFR(HER1) inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM and 23 nM, >10-fold selectivity for HER1/2 than HER4, less potent to MEK1/5, c-Met, Aurora B, Lck, CSK etc. Phase 1.
GDC-0068 is a highly selective pan-Akt inhibitor targeting Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 5 nM/18 nM/8 nM, 620-fold selectivity over PKA. Phase 2.
Torin 1 is a potent inhibitor of mTORC1/2 with IC50 of 2 nM/10 nM; exhibits 1000-fold selectivity for mTOR than PI3K.
GW5074 is a potent and selective c-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 9 nM, no effect on the activities of JNK1/2/3, MEK1, MKK6/7, CDK1/2, c-Src, p38 MAP, VEGFR2 or c-Fms is noted.

S-Ruxolitinib is the chirality of INCB018424, which is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3. Phase 3.
Piceatannol, a natural stilbene, is a selective Syk inhibitor and ~10-fold selectivity versus Lyn.
CZC24832 is the first selective PI3Kγ inhibitor with IC50 of 27 nM, with 10-fold selectivity over PI3Kβ and >100-fold selectivity over PI3Kα and PI3Kδ.
LDK378 is potent inhibitor against ALK with IC50 of 0.2 nM, shows 40- and 35-fold selectivity against IGF-1R and InsR, respectively. Phase 2.
10058-F4 is a c-Myc inhibitor that specificallly inhibits the c-Myc-Max interaction and prevents transactivation of c-Myc target gene expression.
CH5424802 is a potent ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 nM, sensitive to L1196M mutation and higher selectivity for ALK than PF-02341066, NVP-TAE684 and PHA-E429. Phase 1/2.
INCB28060 is a novel, ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-MET with IC50 of 0.13 nM, inactive against RONβ, as well as EGFR and HER-3. Phase 1.

INK 128 is a potent and selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM; >200-fold less potent to class I PI3K isoforms, superior in blocking mTORC1/2 and sensitive to pro-invasion genes (vs Rapamycin). Phase 1.
SAR131675 is a VEGFR3 inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 23 nM/12 nM, about 50- and 10-fold more selective for VEGFR3 than VEGFR1/2, little activity against Akt1, CDKs, PLK1, EGFR, IGF-1R, c-Met, Flt2 etc.
IKK 16 is a selective IκB kinase (IKK) inhibitor for IKK-2, IKK complex and IKK-1 with IC50 of 40 nM, 70 nM and 200 nM, respectively.

PF-477736 is a selective, potent and ATP-competitive Chk1 inhibitor with Ki of 0.49 nM and also inhibits VEGFR2, Aurora-A, FGFR3, Flt3, Fms (CSF1R), Ret and Yes. It shows ~100-fold selectivity for Chk1 than Chk2. Phase 1.

SC-514 is an orally active, ATP-competitive IKK-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 3-12 μM, blocks NF-κB-dependent gene expression, does not inhibit other IKK isoforms or other serine-threonine and tyrosine kinases.
IPI-145 (INK1197) is a novel and selective PI3K δ/γ inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 23 pM/243 pM and 1 nM/50 nM, highly selective for PI3K δ/γ than other protein kinases. Phase 2.
IPA-3 is a selective non-ATP competitive Pak1 inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 μM, no inhibition to group II PAKs (PAKs 4-6).
LY2835219 is a potent and selective inhibitor of CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of 2 nM and 10 nM, respectively.

3-Methyladenine is a selective PI3K inhibitor for Vps34 and PI3Kγ with IC50 of 25 μM and 60 μM;  blocks class I PI3K consistently, whereas suppression of class III PI3K is transient, and also blocks autophagosome formation.
Tofacitinib is a novel inhibitor of JAK3 with IC50 of 1 nM, 20- to 100-fold less potent against JAK2 and JAK1.
BYL719 is a potent and selective PI3Kα inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, and minimal effect on PI3Kβ/γ/δ. Phase 1/2.

BI-D1870 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of S6 ribosome for RSK1/2/3/4 with IC50 of 31 nM/24 nM/18 nM/15 nM, respectively; 10- to 100-fold selectivity for RSK than MST2, GSK-3β, MARK3, CK1 and Aurora B.

PF-562271 is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs.
Go 6983 is a pan-PKC inhibitor against for PKCα, PKCβ, PKCγ and PKCδ with IC50 of 7 nM, 7 nM, 6 nM and 10 nM, respectively; less potent to PKCζ and inactive to PKCμ.
Tofacitinib citrate (CP-690550 citrate) is a novel inhibitor of JAK3 with IC50 of 1 nM, 20- to 100-fold less potent against JAK2 and JAK1.
XL388 is a highly potent, selective, ATP-competitive inhibitor of  mTOR with IC50 of 9.9 nM, 1000-fold selectivity over the closely related PI3K kinases.
VE-822 is an ATR inhibitor with IC50 of 19 nM.
SSR128129E is an orally-active and allosteric FGFR1 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 μM, while not affecting other related RTKs.

Dinaciclib (SCH727965) is a novel and potent CDK inhibitor for CDK2, CDK5, CDK1 and CDK9 with IC50 of 1 nM, 1 nM, 3 nM and 4 nM, respectively. It also blocks thymidine (dThd) DNA incorporation. Phase 3.
Sotrastaurin is a potent and selective pan-PKC inhibitor, mostly for PKCθ with Ki of 0.22 nM; inactive to PKCζ. Phase 1/2.
Tyrphostin AG 879 potently inhibits HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 1 μM, 100- and 500-fold higher selective to ErbB2 than PDGFR and EGFR.
Semaxanib (SU5416) is a potent and selective VEGFR(Flk-1/KDR) inhibitor with IC50 of 1.23 μM, 20-fold more selective for VEGFR than PDGFRβ, lack of activity against EGFR, InsR and FGFR. Phase 3.
NU7026 is a potent DNA-PK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.23 μM, 60-fold selective for DNA-PK than PI3K and inactive against both ATM and ATR.
BAY 11-7082 is a NF-κB inhibitor, inhibits TNFα-induced IκBα phosphorylation with IC50 of 10 μM.
Fingolimod (FTY720) is a S1P antagonist with IC50 of 0.033 nM.
XL019 is a potent and selective JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 2.2 nM, exhibiting >50-fold selectivity over JAK1, JAK3 and TYK2. Phase 1.
AZD3463 is a novel orally bioavailable ALK inhibitor with Ki of 0.75 nM, which also inhibits IGF1R with equivalent potency.
AVL-292 is a covalent, orally active, and highly selective BTK inhibitor with IC50 of <0.5 nM, displaying at least 1400-fold selectivity over the other kinases assayed. Phase 1.
SKI II is a highly selective and non ATP-competitive S1P receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 μM, while exhibits no inhibitory on other kinases including PI3K, PKCα and ERK2.
CO-1686 is an irreversible, mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with Ki of 21.5 nM and 303.3 nM for EGFRL858R/T790M and EGFRWT, respectively. Phase 1/2.
GSK2636771 is a potent, orally bioavailable, PI3Kβ-selective inhibitor, sensitive to PTEN null cell lines. Phase 1/2a.
TCS 359 is a potent FLT3 inhibitor with IC50 of 42 nM.
Pacritinib (SB1518) is a potent and selective inhibitor of Janus Kinase 2 (JAK2) and Fms-Like Tyrosine Kinase-3 (FLT3) with IC50s of 23 and 22 nM, respectively.
GW2580 is a selective CSF-1R inhibitor for c-FMS with IC50 of 30 nM, 150- to 500-fold selective compared to b-Raf, CDK4, c-KIT, c-SRC, EGFR, ERBB2/4, ERK2, FLT-3, GSK3, ITK, JAK2 etc.
ID-8 is a DYRK inhibitor, and sustains embryonic stem cell self-renewal in long-term culture.
Lenalidomide (CC-5013) is a TNF-α secretion inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM.
TW-37 is a novel nonpeptide inhibitor to recombinant Bcl-2, Bcl-xL and Mcl-1 with Ki of 0.29 μM, 1.11 μM and 0.26 μM, respectively.
Ganetespib is an HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM in OSA 8 cells, induces apoptosis of OSA cells while normal osteoblasts are not affected; active metabolite of STA-1474.
GZD824 is a novel orally bioavailable Bcr-Abl inhibitor for Bcr-Abl(WT) and Bcr-Abl(T315I) with IC50 of 0.34 nM and 0.68 nM, respectively.
TAK-632 is a potent pan-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 8.3 nM and 1.4 nM for B-Raf(wt) and C-Raf, respectively, showing less or no inhibition against other tested kinases.
PQ401 inhibits autophosphorylation of IGF-1R domain with IC50 of <1 μM.
Tyrphostin AG 1296 is an inhibitor of PDGFR with IC50 of 0.3-0.5 μM, no activity to EGFR.
p276-00 is a novel CDK1, CDK4 and CDK9 inhibitor with IC50 of 79 nM, 63 nM and 20 nM, respectively.
PD153035 is a potent and specific inhibitor of EGFR with Ki and IC50 of 5.2 pM and 29 pM, respectively.
AZ191 is a potent and selective DYRK1B inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM, about 5- and 110-fold selectivity over DYRK1A and DYRK2, respectively.
STF-62247 shows selectivtoxicity and growth inhibition of renal cells lacking VHL; 25-fold greater sensitivity observed for cells with VHL deficiency compared to wild-type (VHL+).

YM155 is a potent survivin suppressant by inhibiting Survivin promoter activity with IC50 of 0.54 nM; does not significantly inhibit SV40 promoter activity, but is observed to slightly inhibit the interaction of Survivin with XIAP. Phase 1/2.

ABT-751 (E7010) binds to the colchicine site on β-tubulin and inhibits polymerization of microtubules, not a substrate for the MDR transporter and is active against cell lines resistant to vincristine, doxorubicin, and cisplatin. Phase 1/2.
RKI-1447 is a potent inhibitor of ROCK1 and ROCK2, with IC50 of 14.5 nM and 6.2 nM, respectively, has anti-invasive and antitumor activities.
ZCL278 is a selective Cdc42 GTPase inhibitor with Kd of 11.4 μM.
ZM 39923 is an JAK1/3 inhibitor with pIC50 of 4.4/7.1, almost no activity to JAK2 and modestly potent to EGFR; also found to be sensitive to transglutaminase.
NSC 23766 is an inhibitor of Rac GTPase targeting Rac activation by guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) with IC50 of ~50 μM; does not inhibit the closely related  targets, Cdc42 or RhoA.
Bardoxolone Methyl is an IKK inhibitor, showing potent proapoptotic and anti-inflammatory activities. Phase 3.
PD 0332991 (Palbociclib) Isethionate is the isethionate of PD 0332991, a highly specific inhibitor of CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of 11 nM and 16 nM, respectively.
UNC2250 is a potent and selective Mer inhibitor with IC50 of 1.7 nM, about 160- and 60-fold selectivity over the closely related kinases Axl/Tyro3.
Elesclomol (STA-4783) is a novel potent oxidative stress inducer that elicits pro-apoptosis events among tumor cells.
Andarine is a selective non-steroidal androgen receptor (AR) agonist with Ki of 4 nM, tissue-selective for anabolic organs.
Cisplatin is an inorganic platinum complex, which is able to inhibit DNA synthesis by conforming DNA adducts.
BIO (6-bromoindirubin-3'-oxime) is a specific inhibitor of GSK-3 with IC50 of 5 nM for GSK-3α/β, shows >16-fold selectivity over CDK5, also a pan-JAK inhibitor.
WZ4003 is a highly specific NUAK kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM and 100 nM for NUAK1 and NUAK2, respectively, without significant inhibition on 139 other kinases.
SMI-4a is a potent inhibitor of Pim1 with IC50 of 17 nM, modest potent to Pim-2, does not significantly inhibit other serine/threonine- or tyrosine-kinases.
PRT062607 (P505-15) HCl is a novel, highly selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM, >80-fold selective for Syk than Fgr, Lyn, FAK, Pyk2 and Zap70.
DMXAA (Vadimezan) is a vascular disrupting agents (VDA) and competitive inhibitor of DT-diaphorase with Ki of 20 μM and IC50 of 62.5 μM, respectively. Phase 3.
CP-466722 is an potent and reversible ATM inhibitor.
LEE011 is an orally available, and highly specific CDK4/6 inhibitor.
Obatoclax (GX15-070) is an antagonist of Bcl-2 with Ki of 0.22 μM, can assist in overcoming MCL-1 mediated resistance to apoptosis. Phase 1/2.
17-AAG is a potent HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, having a 100-fold higher binding affinity for HSP90 derived from tumour cells than HSP90 from normal cells.

JNJ-26854165 acts as a HDM2 ubiquitin ligase antagonist and also induces early apoptosis in p53 wild-type cells, inhibits cellular proliferation followed by delayed apoptosis in the absence of functional p53. Phase 1.

Ro 31-8220 is a pan-PKC inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, 24 nM, 14 nM, 27 nM, and 24 nM for PKC-α, PKC-βI, PKC-βII, PKC-γ, and PKC-ε, respectively, and also shows potent inhibition against MAPKAP-K1b, MSK1, GSK3β and S6K1.
EHop-016 is a specific Rac GTPase inhibitor with IC50 of 1.1 μM for Rac1, equally potent inhibition for Rac3.
VE-821 is a potent and selective ATP competitive inhibitor of ATR with Ki/IC50 of 13 nM/26 nM, shows inhibition of H2AX phosphorylation, minimal activity against PIKKs ATM, DNA-PK, mTOR and PI3Kγ.
Butein, a plant polyphenol isolated from Rhus verniciflua, is able to inhibit the activation of protein tyrosine kinase, NF-κB and STAT3, also inhibits EGFR
GW441756 is a potent, selective inhibitor of TrkA with IC50 of 2 nM, with very little activity to c-Raf1 and CDK2.
PF-03814735 is a novel, potent and reversible inhibitor of both Aurora A and Aurora B with IC50 of 0.8 nM and 5 nM, respectively.
ML167 is a highly selective Cdc2-like kinase 4 (Clk4) inhibitor with IC50 of 136 nM, >10-fold selectivity for closely related kinases Clk1-3 and Dyrk1A/1B.
Nutlin-3 is a potent and selective Mdm2 (RING finger-dependent ubiquitin protein ligase for itself and p53) antagonist with IC50 of 90 nM; stabilizes p73 in p53-deficient cells.
17-DMAG is a potent, water-soluble HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 62 nM.
MK-2866 (GTx-024) is a selective androgen receptor modulator (SARM) with Ki of 3.8 nM, and is tissue-selective for anabolic organs. Phase 3.
Skepinone-L is a selective p38α-MAPK inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM.

TG003 is a potent and ATP-competitive Cdc2-like kinase (Clk) inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM, 200 nM, and 15 nM for Clk1, Clk2, and Clk4, respectively. No inhibitory effect on Clk3, SRPK1, SRPK2, or PKC.
AG-18 inhibits EGFR with IC50 of 35 μM.
GDC-0349 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with Ki of 3.8 nM, 790-fold inhibitory effect against PI3Kα and other 266 kinases. Phase 1.
SKLB1002 is a potent and ATP-competitive VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 32 nM.
LGX818 is a highly potent RAF inhibitor with selective anti-proliferative and apoptotic activity in cells expressing B-RAF(V600E) with EC50 of 4 nM.
ABT-263 (Navitoclax) is a potent inhibitor of Bcl-xL, Bcl-2 and Bcl-w with Ki of ≤ 0.5 nM, ≤1 nM and ≤1 nM, but binds more weakly to Mcl-1 and A1. Phase 1/2.
SB431542 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ALK5 with IC50 of 94 nM, 100-fold more selective for ALK5 than p38 MAPK and other kinases.
Docetaxel, an analog of taxol, is an inhibitor of depolymerisation of microtubules by binding to stabilized microtubules.
BIIB021 is an orally available, fully synthetic small-molecule inhibitor of HSP90 with Ki and EC50 of 1.7 nM and 38 nM, respectively.
