AZD2858 is a selective GSK-3 inhibitor with an IC50 of 68 nM, activating Wnt signaling, increases bone mass in rats.
Sorafenib is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM, respectively.

CEP-32496 is a highly potent inhibitor of BRAF(V600E/WT) and c-Raf with Kd of 14 nM/36 nM and 39 nM, also potent to Abl-1, c-Kit, Ret, PDGFRβ and VEGFR2, respectively; insignificant affinity for MEK-1, MEK-2, ERK-1 and ERK-2. Phase 1/2.
BMS-345541 is a highly selective inhibitor of the catalytic subunits of IKK-2 and IKK-1 with IC50 of 0.3 μM and 4 μM, respectively.

PF-562271 HCl is the hydrochloride salt of PF-562271, which is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs. Phase 1.
1-Azakenpaullone is a potent and selective GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM, >100-fold selectivity over CDK1/cyclin B and CDK5/p25.
ABT-737 is a BH3 mimetic inhibitor of Bcl-xL, Bcl-2 and Bcl-w with EC50 of 78.7 nM, 30.3 nM and 197.8 nM, respectively; no inhibition observed against Mcl-1, Bcl-B or Bfl-1. Phase 2.

AUY922 (NVP-AUY922) is a highly potent HSP90 inhibitor for HSP90α/β with IC50 of 13 nM /21 nM, weaker potency against the HSP90 family members GRP94 and TRAP-1, exhibits the tightest binding of any small-molecule HSP90 ligand. Phase 1/2.
Paclitaxel is a microtubule polymer stabilizer with IC50 of 0.1 pM in human endothelial cells.
XAV-939 selectively inhibits Wnt/β-catenin-mediated transcription through tankyrase1/2 inhibition with IC50 of 11 nM/4 nM, regulates axin levels and does not affect CRE, NF-κB or TGF-β.
CNX-774 is an irreversible, orally active, and highly selective BTK inhibitor with IC50 of <1 nM.
AR-A014418 is an ATP-competitive, and selective GSK3β inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of 104 nM and 38 nM, without significant inhibition on 26 other kinases tested.
AZD5363 potently inhibits all isoforms of Akt(Akt1/Akt2/Akt3) with IC50 of 3 nM/8 nM/8 nM, similar to P70S6K/PKA and lower activity towards ROCK1/2. Phase 1/2.
ETP-46464 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ATR with IC50 of 25 nM.
GS-9973 is an orally bioavailable, selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 7.7 nM. Phase 2.
SRPIN340 is a selective SRPK inhibitor with Ki of 0.89 μM for SRPK1, showing no significant inhibitory activity against more than 140 other kinases..
Bortezomib (PS-341) is a potent 20S proteasome inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM.
BTZ043 racemate is a decaprenylphosphoryl-β-D-ribose 2'-epimerase (DprE1) inhibitor acting as a new antimycobacterial agent that kill Mycobacterium tuberculosis.
Capecitabine is a tumor-selective fluoropyrimidine carbamate which achieves higher intratumoral 5-FU level with lower toxicity than 5-FU.
BIBR 1532 is a potent, selective, non-competitive telomerase inhibitor with IC50 of 100 nM.
Anastrozole is a third-generation nonsteroidal selective aromatase inhibitor.
Dimesna is an uroprotective agent used to decrease urotoxicity.
Carboplatin is a DNA synthesis inhibitor by binding to DNA and interfering with the cell's repair mechanism.
Topotecan (NSC 609699) is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for MCF-7 Luc cells and DU-145 Luc cells with IC50 of 13 nM and 2 nM, respectively.
Carmofur is a pyrimidine analogue used as an antineoplastic agent.
Epothilone B is a Taxol-like microtubule-stabilizing agent with EC0.01 of 1.8 μM. Phase 2.

CHR-2797 is an aminopeptidase inhibitor for LAP, PuSA and Aminopeptidase N with IC50 of 100 nM, 150 nM and 220 nM, respectively, and does not effectively inhibit either PILSAP, MetAP-2, LTA4 hydrolase, or MetAP-2. Phase 2.
Ezetimibe (Zetia) is a compound that lowers cholesterol.
Azathioprine(Azasan, Imuran) is a drug that suppresses the immune system and is used in organ transplantation and autoimmune disease.
Fluvastatin Sodium inhibits HMG-CoA reductase activity with IC50 of 8 nM.
Aprepitant is a potent and selective neurokinin-1 receptor antagonist.
Doxorubicin (Adriamycin) is an antibiotic agent that inhibits DNA topoisomerase II and induces DNA damage and apoptosis.
Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase.
Letrozole is a third generation inhibitor of aromatase with IC50 of 0.07-20 nM.
Epothilone A is a Taxol-like microtubule-stabilizing agent with EC0.01 of 2 μM.
It was developed to be used as a chemotherapy medication for the treatment of brain cancer, pancreatic cancer and more.
MK-1775 is a potent and selective Wee1 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.2 nM; hinders G2 DNA damage checkpoint. Phase 2.
Aminoglutethimide is an aromatase inhibitor with IC50 of 10 μM.
Mesna(Uromitexan, Mesnex), a sulfhydryl compound that is used to reduce the incidence of hemorrhagic cystitis associated with certain chemotherapeutic agents.
Maraviroc is a CCR5 antagonist for MIP-1α, MIP-1β and RANTES with IC50 of 3.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 5.2 nM, respectively.
Bicalutamide is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 0.16 μM.
Fluorouracil (5-Fluoracil, 5-FU) is an DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor, which interrupts nucleotide synthetic by inhibiting thymidylate synthase (TS).
Dacarbazine is an antineoplastic chemotherapy drug used in the treatment of various cancers.
Temozolomide is a DNA damage inducer.
Floxuridine is a prodrugs of floxuridine and an oncology agent with an GI50 of 5.1 μM for the inhibition of MDCK/PEPT1.
Zileuton is an orally active inhibitor of 5-lipoxygenase, and thus inhibits leukotrienes (LTB4, LTC4, LTD4, and LTE4) formation.
Febuxostat is selective xanthine oxidase inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM.
Disulfiram is an agent used to support the treatment of chronic alcoholism by producing an acute sensitivity to alcohol.
Teniposide(Vumon)is a chemotherapeutic medication mainly used in the treatment of childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia (ALL).
Bexarotene is a retinoid specifically selective for retinoid X receptors, used as an oral antineoplastic agent in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma.
Raltitrexed is a thymidylate synthase inhibitor with an IC50 of 9 nM for the inhibition of L1210 cell growth.
Methotrexate is an antimetabolite and antifolate drug, which acts by inhibiting the metabolism of folic acid.
Epirubicin HCl, a semisynthetic L-arabino derivative of doxorubicin, is an antineoplastic agent by inhibiting Topoisomerase.
Vincristine is an inhibitor of polymerization of microtubules by binding to tubulin with IC50 of 32 μM.
FT-207 (NSC 148958) is a substance being used in the treatment of some types of cancer.

Ispinesib (SB-715992, CK0238273) is a potent, specific and reversible inhibitor of kinesin spindle protein (KSP) with Ki app of 1.7 nM, no inhibition to CENP-E, RabK6, MCAK, MKLP1, KHC or Kif1A. Phase 1/2.
Pomalidomide inhibits LPS-induced TNF-α release with IC50 of 13 nM.
Meprednisone is a glucocorticoid and a methylated derivative of prednisone.
Simvastatin is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with Ki of 0.1-0.2 nM .

MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50 and Ki of 3.4 nM and 0.93 nM, respectively, also inhibits the caspase-like (β1) and trypsin-like (β2) proteolytic sites, with IC50 of 31 and 3500 nM.

Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug, immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers. Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase, which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.Phase 3.
Imiquimod is a novel synthetic agent with immune response modifying activity.
Oxaliplatin inhibits DNA synthesis by conforming DNA adducts.
Vinblastine inhibits microtubule formation and supresses nAChR activity with IC50 of 8.9 μM.Phase 2.
Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.
Tipifarnib (R115777) is a potent and specific farnesyltransferase (FTase) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.6 nM, its anti-proliferative effects are most prominent in H-ras or N-ras mutant cells. Phase 3.
Prednisone (Adasone) is a synthetic corticosteroid agent that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant compound.
Busulfan(Myleran, Busulfex) is a cell cycle non-specific alkylating antineoplastic agent.
Ranolazine(Ranexa) is an antianginal medication.

MLN9708 immediately hydrolyzed to MLN2238, the biologically active form, on exposure to aqueous solutions or plasma. MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50/Ki of 3.4 nM/0.93 nM, less potent to β1 and little activity to β2. Phase 3.
Exemestane is an aromatase inhibitor, inhibits human placental and rat ovarian aromatase with IC50 of 30 nM and 40 nM, respectively.
Bendamustine HCL is a DNA-damaging agent with IC50 of 50 μM.
Etoposide is a semisynthetic derivative of podophyllotoxin, which inhibits DNA synthesis via topoisomerase II  inhibition activity.
Enzalutamide (MDV3100) is an androgen-receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 36 nM.

Mercaptopurine is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.
Doxercalciferol is a synthetic analog of vitamin D.
Triamcinolone Acetonide is a more potent type of triamcinolone, being about 8 times as effective as prednisone.
Hydrocortisone is a steroid hormone or glucocorticoid produced by the adrenal gland.
Lomustine inhibits cancer cells by damaging the DNA and stops cells from dividing.
SB743921 is a kinesin spindle protein (KSP) inhibitor with Ki of 0.1 nM, almost no affinity to MKLP1, Kin2, Kif1A, Kif15, KHC, Kif4 and CENP-E. Phase 1/2.
Irinotecan is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for LoVo cells and HT-29 cells with IC50 of 15.8 μM and 5.17 μM, respectively.
Nelarabine is a purine nucleoside analog and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 from 0.067-2.15 μM in tumor cells.
Idarubicin HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of Idarubicin which is an anthracycline antibiotic and a DNA topoisomerase II (topo II) inhibitor for MCF-7 cells with IC50 of 3.3 ng/mL.
Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM.
Streptozotocin is a glucosamine-nitrosourea derivative, which is a methylating, carcinogenic, antibiotic and diabetes inducing agent.
SB525334 is a potent and selective inhibitor of TGFβ receptor I (ALK5) with IC50 of 14.3 nM, is 4-fold less potent to ALK4 than ALK5 and inactive to ALK2, 3, and 6.
Cytarabine (Cytosine arabinoside, AraC) is an antimetabolic agent and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM in wild-type CCRF-CEM cells.
Estradiol is the predominant sex hormone.
Hydroxyurea is an antineoplastic agent that inhibits DNA synthesis through the inhibition of ribonucleoside diphosphate reductase.
Formestane(Lentaron(R)) is a second generation selective aromatase inhibitor with an IC50 of 80 nM.
Cladribine is an adenosine deaminase inhibitor for U266, RPMI8226, and MM1.S cells with IC50 of approximately 2.43 μM, 0.75 μM, and 0.18 μM, respectively.
Bleomycin Sulfate is a glycopeptide antibiotic and an anticancer agent for squamous cell carcinomas (SCC) with IC50 of 4 nM in UT-SCC-19A cells.
Fludarabine Phosphate is an analogue of adenosine and deoxyadenosine, which is able to compete with dATP for incorporation into DNA and inhibit DNA synthesis.
Altretamine is an anti-neoplastic agent.
Dexamethasone is an anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant.
Mycophenolate Mofetil is a non-competitive, selective and reversible inhibitor of inosine monophosphate dehydrogenase I/II with IC50 of 39 nM and 27 nM, respectively.

All−trans Retinoic acid (ATRA), whith is a ligand for both the retinoic acid receptor (RAR) and the retinoid X receptor (RXR), can induce granulocytic differentiation and apoptosis in acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL) cells.
Gemcitabine(Gemzar) belongs to the group of medicines called antimetabolites.Phase 3.
Flutamide is an antiandrogen drug, with its active metablolite binding at androgen receptor with Ki values of 55 nM, and primarily used to treat prostate cancer. Phase 4.
DAPT (GSI-IX) is a novel γ-secretase inhibitor, which inhibits Aβ production with IC50 of 20 nM in HEK 293 cells.
SB505124 is a selective inhibitor of TGFβR for ALK4, ALK5 with IC50 of 129 nM and 47 nM, respectively, also inhibits ALK7, but does not inhibit ALK1, 2, 3, or 6.
Ciprofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor agonist.
GW9662 is a selective PPAR antagonist for PPARγ with IC50 of 3.3 nM, with at least 100 to 1000-fold functional selectivity in cells with PPARγversus PPARα and PPARδ.
SN-38 is an active metabolite of CPT-11, inhibits DNA topoisomerase I, DNA synthesis and causes frequent DNA single-strand breaks.
KY02111 promotes differentiation of hPSCs to cardiomyocytes by inhibiting Wnt signaling, may act downstream of APC and GSK3β.
Mdivi-1 is a selective cell-permeable inhibitor of mitochondrial division DRP1 (dynamin-related GTPase) and mitochondrial division Dynamin I (Dnm1) with IC50 of 1-10 μM.
CRT0044876 is a potent and selective APE1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~3 μM.
Veliparib (ABT-888) is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 and PARP2 with Ki of 5.2 nM and 2.9 nM, respectively. It is inactive to SIRT2. Phase 1/2.
BSI-201 (Iniparib, SAR240550) is a PARP1 inhibitor with demonstrated effectiveness in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC). Phase 3.

Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate) is a HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 mM and also inhibits GABA-transaminase or succinic
semialdehyde dehydrogenase.
VX-765 is a potent and selective inhibitor of caspase-1 with Ki of 0.8 nM.
KW-2478 is a nonansamycin HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.8 nM. Phase 1/2

Apoptosis Activator 2 strongly induces caspase-3 activation, PARP cleavage, and DNA fragmentation which leads to the destruction of cells (Apaf-1 dependent) with IC50 of ~4 μM, inactive to HMEC, PREC, or MCF-10A cells.
GDC-0152 is a potent antagonist of XIAP-BIR3, ML-IAP-BIR3, cIAP1-BIR3 and cIAP2-BIR3 with Ki of 28 nM, 14 nM, 17 nM and 43 nM, respectively; less affinity shown to cIAP1-BIR2 and cIAP2-BIR2. Phase 1.
BAM 7 is a direct and selective activator of proapoptotic Bax with EC50 of 3.3 μM.
RepSox is a potent and selective inhibitor of the TGFβR-1/ALK5 with IC50 of 23 nM and 4 nM for ATP binding to ALK5 and ALK5 autophosphorylation, respectively.
VER-49009 is a potent HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 47 nM for HSP90β.
FG-4592 is an HIF α prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor, stabilizes HIF-2 and induces EPO production. Phase 2/3.
PCI-24781 is a novel pan-HDAC inhibitor mostly targeting HDAC1 with Ki of 7 nM, modest potent to HDACs 2, 3, 6, and 10 and greater than 40-fold selectivity against HDAC8. Phase 1/2.
Decitabine is a potent inhibitor of DNA methylation with IC50 of 438 nM and 4.38 nM in HL-60 and KG1a cells, respectively.
Cryptotanshinone (CPT) is a STAT3 inhibitor with IC50 of 4.6 μM, strongly inhibits phosphorylation of STAT3 Tyr705, with a small effect on STAT3 Ser727, but none against STAT1 nor STAT5.
GW788388 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ALK5 with IC50 of 18 nM, also inhibits TGF-β type II receptor and activin type II receptor activities, but does not inhibit BMP type II receptor.
Pifithrin-α is an inhibitor of p53, inhibiting p53-dependent transactivation of p53-responsive genes.
Birinapant is a SMAC mimetic antagonist, mostly to cIAP1 with Kd of <1 nM, less potent to XIAP. Phase 1/2.
XL888 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of HSP90 with IC50 of 24 nM.
Beta-Lapachone is a selective DNA topoisomerase I inhibitor, exhibiting no inhibitory activities against DNA topoisomerase II or ligase. Phase 2.
Triapine is a potent ribonucleotide reductase inhibitor with broad spectrum antitumor activity by inhibiting DNA synthesis. Phase 2.
Panobinostat (LBH589) is a novel broad-spectrum HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM. Phase 3.
LAQ824 (Dacinostat) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 32 nM and is known to activate the p21 promoter.
PFI-1 is a selective BET (bromodomain-containing protein) inhibitor for BRD4 with IC50 of 0.22 μM.
Astragaloside A (Astragaloside IV) is the primary pure saponin isolated from Astragalus membranaceus, which has been widely used for the treatment of cardiovascular diseases.
RITA (NSC 652287) induces both DNA-protein and DNA-DNA cross-links with no detectable DNA single-strand breaks, and also inhibits MDM2-p53 interaction by targeting p53.
Pifithrin-μ is a specific p53 inhibitor by reducing its affinity to Bcl-xL and Bcl-2, and also inhibits HSP70 function and autophagy.
Stattic, the first nonpeptidic small molecule, potently inhibits STAT3 activation and nuclear translocation with IC50 of 5.1 μM, highly selectivity over STAT1.
LGK-974 is a potent and specific PORCN inhibitor, and inhibits Wnt signaling with IC50 of 0.4 nM. Phase 1.
NMS-E973 is a potent and selective Hsp90 inhibitor with DC50 of <10 nM for Hsp90 binding, no activiy against a panel of 52 diverse protein kinases.
MPI-0479605 is an ATP competitive and selective inhibitor of mitotic kinase Mps1 with IC50 of 1.8 nM, >40-fold selectivity over other kinases.
Trichostatin A (TSA) is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of ~1.8 nM – HDAC8 is the only known member of the HDAC-family that is not affected by TSA. Phase 3.

JNJ-26481585 is a novel second-generation HDAC inhibitor with highest potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.11 nM, modest potent to HDACs 2, 4, 10, and 11; greater than 30-fold selectivity against HDACs 3, 5, 8, and 9 and lowest potency to HDACs 6 and 7. Phase 2.
2-Methoxyestradiol depolymerizes microtubules and blocks HIF-1α nuclear accumulation and HIF-transcriptional activity. Phase 2.
Resveratrol is a phytoalexin produced naturally by several plants with anti-cancer, anti-inflammatory, blood-sugar-lowering and other beneficial cardiovascular effects.
AG14361 is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 with Ki of <5 nM. It is at least 1000-fold more potent than the benzamides.
RG108 is an inhibitor of DNA methyltransferase with IC50 of 115 nM, does not cause trapping of covalent enzymes.
AZD2461 is a novel PARP inhibitor with low affinity for Pgp than Olaparib. Phase 1.
Zebularine is a DNA methylation inhibitor that forms a covalent complex with DNA methyltransferases, also inhibits cytidinedeaminase with Ki of 2 μM.
SGC-CBP30 is a potent CREBBP/EP300 inhibitor with IC50 of 21 nM and 38 nM, respectively.
ME0328 is a potent and selective PARP inhibitor with IC50 of 0.89 μM for PARP3, about 7-fold selectivity over PARP1.
GSK343 is a potent and selective EZH2 inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM, showing 60 fold selectivity against EZH1, and >1000 fold selectivity against other histone methyltransferases.
MS436 is a selective BET bromodomain inhibitor with Ki of <0.085 μM and 0.34 μM for BRD4 (1) and BRD4 (2), respectively
Remodelin is a potent acetyl-transferase NAT10 inhibitor.

Droxinostat (CMH, 5809354) is a selective inhibitor of HDAC, mostly for HDACs 6 and 8 with IC50 of 2.47μM and 1.46 μM, greater than 8-fold selective against HDAC3 and no inhibition to HDAC1, 2, 4, 5, 7, 9, and 10.
AR-42 is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 30 nM.
Baricitinib is a selective JAK1 and JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.9 nM and 5.7 nM, ~70 and ~10-fold selective versus JAK3 and Tyk2, no inhibition to c-Met and Chk2. Phase 3.
EPZ004777 HCl is the hydrochloride salt of EPZ004777, which is a potent, selective DOT1L inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 nM.
3-deazaneplanocin A (DZNeP), an analog of adenosine, is a competitive inhibitor of S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase with Ki of 50 pM.
MM-102 is a high-affinity peptidomimetic MLL1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 μM.
Nexturastat A is a potent and selective HDAC6 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, >190-fold selectivity over other HDACs.
EI1 is a potent and selective EZH2 inhibitor with IC50 of 15 nM and 13 nM for EZH2 (WT) and EZH2 (Y641F), respectively.
GSK1324726A (I-BET726) is a highly selective inhibitor of BET family proteins with IC50 of 41 nM, 31 nM, and 22 nM for BRD2, BRD3, and BRD4, respectively.
Splitomicin is a selective NAD(+)-dependent histone deacetylase Sir2p inhibitor with IC50 of 60 μM, showing a higher activity in a cell-based assay.
MC1568 is a selective HDAC inhibitor for maize HD1-A with IC50 of 100 nM. It is 34-fold more selective for HD1-A than HD1-B.
Tubastatin A is a potent and selective HDAC6 inhibitor with IC50 of 15 nM. It is selective (1000-fold more) against all other isozymes except HDAC8 (57-fold more).
PJ-34 is a PARP inhibitor with EC50 of 20 nM and is equally potent to PARP1/2.
BMN 673 is a novel PARP inhibitor with IC50 of 0.58 nM. It is also a potent inhibitor of PARP-2, but does not inhibit PARG and is highly sensitive to PTEN mutation. Phase 1.
EPZ-6438 is a potent, and selective EZH2 inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 2.5 nM and 11 nM, exhibiting a 35-fold selectivity versus EZH1 and >4,500-fold selectivity relative to 14 other HMTs.
SGI-1027 is a DNMT inhibitor with IC50 of 6, 8, 7.5 μM for DNMT1, DNMT3A, and DNMT3B

Rocilinostat (ACY-1215) is a selective HDAC6 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM. It is >10-fold more selective for HDAC6 than HDAC1/2/3 (class I HDACs) with slight activity against HDAC8, minimal activity against HDAC4/5/7/9/11, Sirtuin1, and Sirtuin2.
BRD4770 is a histone methyltransferase G9a inhibitor with IC50 of 6.3 μM, and induces cell senescence
PFI-3 is a selective chemical probe for SMARCA bromodomains, including SMARCA2, SMARCA4 and PB1(5) bromodomains.
AGK2 is a potent, and selective SIRT2 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.5 μM.
SB939 is a potent pan-HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 40-140 nM with exception for HDAC6. It has no activity against the class III isoenzyme SIRT I. Phase 2.
Resminostat dose-dependently and selectively inhibits HDAC1/3/6 with IC50 of 42.5 nM/50.1 nM/71.8 nM, less potent to HDAC8 with IC50 of 877 nM.
IOX2 is a potent inhibitor of HIF-1α prolyl hydroxylase-2 (PHD2) with IC50 of 21 nM, >100-fold selectivity over JMJD2A, JMJD2C, JMJD2E, JMJD3, or the 2OG oxygenase FIH.

EPZ-5676 is an S-adenosyl methionine (SAM) competitive inhibitor of protein methyltransferase DOT1L with Ki of 80 pM, demonstrating >37,000-fold selectivity against all other PMTs tested, inhibits H3K79 methylation in tumor. Phase 1.
C646 is an inhibitor for histone acetyltransferase, and inhibits p300 with a Ki of 400 nM.  Preferentially selective for p300 versus other acetyltransferases.
RG2833 (RGFP109) is a brain-penetrant HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM and 50 nM for HDAC1 and HDAC3, respectively.

BIX01294 is an inhibitor of G9a histone methyltransferase with IC50 of 2.7 μM, reduces H3K9me2 of bulk histones, also weakly inhibits GLP (primarily H3K9me3), no significant activity observed at other histone methyltransferases.
UNC0631 is a potent histone methyltransferase G9a inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM.
CPI-203 is a potent BET bromodomain inhibitor with IC50 of 37 nM for BRD4.

UNC1999 is a potent, orally bioavailable and selective inhibitor of EZH2 and EZH1 with IC50 of 2 nM and 45 nM, respectively, showing >1000-fold selectivity over a broad range of epigenetic and non-epigenetic targets.
EX 527 is a potent and selective SIRT1 inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM, exhibits >200-fold selectivity against SIRT2 and SIRT3.
M344 is a potent HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 100 nM and able to induce cell differentiation.
Entacapone inhibits catechol-O-methyltransferase(COMT) with IC50 of 151 nM.

GSK J4 HCl is a cell permeable prodrug of GSK J1, which is the first selective inhibitor of the H3K27 histone demethylase JMJD3 and UTX with IC50 of 60 nM and inactive against a panel of demethylases of the JMJ family.

I-BET-762 is an inhibitor for BET proteins with IC50 of ~35 nM, suppresses the production of proinflammatory proteins by macrophages and blocks acute inflammation, highly selective over other bromodomain-containing proteins.
RVX-208 is a potent BET bromodomain inhibitor with IC50 of 0.510 μM for BD2, about 170-fold selectivity over BD1. Phase 2.
UPF 1069 is a selective PARP2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3 μM. It is ~27-fold selective against PARP1.
MI-2 (Menin-MLL Inhibitor) is a potent menin-MLL interaction inhibitor with IC50 of 446 nM.

Diphenhydramine HCl (Benadryl), a histamine H1 antagonist used as an antiemetic, antitussive, for dermatoses and pruritus, for hypersensitivity reactions, as a hypnotic, an antiparkinson, and as an ingredient in common cold preparations.

Phase 1.

Neostigmine bromide (Prostigmin) is a reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.
Benzethonium chloride is a potent inhibitor of nAChRs, it inhibits α4β2 nAChRs and α7 nAChRs with IC50 of 49 nM and 122 nM, respectively.
CFTRinh-172 is a voltage-independent, selective CFTR inhibitor with Ki of 300 nM, showing no effects on MDR1, ATP-sensitive K+ channels, or a series of other transporters.

CEP-18770 is an orally active inhibitor of the chymotrypsin-like activity of proteasome with IC50 of 3.8 nM, with only marginal inhibition of the tryptic and peptidylglutamyl activities of the proteosome. Phase 1/2.

VX-222 (VCH-222) is a novel, potent and selective inhibitor of HCV polymerase with IC50 of 0.94-1.2 μM, 15.3-fold less effective for mutant M423T, and 108-fold less effective for mutant I482L. Phase 2.
Divalproex sodium consists of a compound of sodium valproate and valproic acid in a 1:1 molar relationship in an enteric coated form.
LY411575 is a potent γ-secretase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.078 nM/0.082 nM (membrane/cell-based), also inhibits Notch clevage with withIC50 of 0.39 nM.
Trifluoperazine is a dopamine D2 receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 1.1 nM.
P22077 is an inhibitor of ubiquitin-specific protease USP7 with EC50 of 8.6 μM, also inhibits the closely related USP47.
Cyclosporin A is an immunosuppressive agent, binds to the cyclophilin and then inhibits calcineurin with IC50 of 7 nM, widely used in organ transplantation to prevent rejection. Phase 4.
Pioglitazone (Actos) is a selective peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor gamma stimulator.
Geldanamycin is a natural existing HSP90 inhibitor with Kd of 1.2 μM, specifically disrupts glucocorticoid receptor (GR)/HSP association.
Triptolide is a diterpene triepoxide, immunosuppresive agent extracted from the Chinese herb Tripterygium wilfordii.
Gemcitabine HCl is a DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 50 nM, 40 nM, 18 nM and 12 nM in PANC1, MIAPaCa2, BxPC3 and Capan2 cells, respectively.
Cyclophosphamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent, it attaches the alkyl group to the guanine base of DNA.
IC-87114 is a selective inhibitor of PI3Kδ with IC50 of 0.5 μM.
APO866 effectively inhibits NAMPT with IC50 of 0.09 nM.
U73122 is a potent phospholipase C (PLC) inhibitor, which reduces agonist-induced Ca2+ increases in platelets and PMN.
Amonafide produces protein-associated DNA-strand breaks through a topoisomerase II-mediated reaction, but does not produce topoisomerase I-mediated DNA cleavage. Phase 3.
Gossypol is a polyphenolic aldehyde that permeates cells and acts as an inhibitor for several dehydrogenase enzymes.
Lonidamine is an orally administered small molecule hexokinase inactivator with an IC50 of 0.85 mM.
AZ3146 is a selective Mps1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~35 nM, contributes to recruitment of CENP-E (kinesin-related motor protein), less potent to FAK, JNK1, JNK2, and Kit.
QNZ (EVP4593) shows potent inhibitory activity toward both NF-κB activation and TNF-α production with IC50 of 11 nM and 7 nM, respectively.
Leucovorin is a reduced folic acid.
Vinpocetine is a selectively inhibitor of voltage-sensitive sodium channel for the treatment of stroke, vascular dementia and Alzheimer's disease.
Bafetinib (INNO-406) is a potent and selective dual Bcr-Abl/Lyn inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM and 19 nM, respectively.
Desmethyl Erlotinib (CP-473420) is a free base of OSI-420, which is an active metabolite of Erlotinib which is an orally active EGFR inhibitor for human EGFR with IC50 of 2 nM.

GANT61 is an inhibitor for GLI1 as well as GLI2-induced transcription, inhibits hedgehog with IC50 of 5 μM, displays selectivity over other pathways, such as TNF and glucocorticoid receptor gene transactivation.
Mizoribine is an imidazole nucleoside, selectively inhibits inosine monophosphate synthetase and guanosine monophosphate synthetase.
Phloretin is a dihydrochalcone found in apple tree leaves, which shows beneficial effects on diabetes.
GW3965 is a potent, selective LXRagonist for hLXRα and hLXRβ with EC50 of 190 and 30 nM, respectively.
PAC-1 is a potent procaspase-3 activator with EC50 of 0.22 μM and the first small molecule known to directly activate procaspase-3 to caspase-3.
JZL 184 is the first selective inhibitor of monoacylglycerol lipase (MAGL) with IC50 of 8 nM.
Pamidronate disodium is a nitrogen containing bisphosphonate, used to prevent osteoporosis.
Lapatinib, used in the form of Lapatinib Ditosylate, is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM, respectively.
Vinorelbine (Navelbine) is an anti-mitotic agent which inhibits the proliferation of Hela cells with IC50 of 1.25 nM.

Fosbretabulin (Combretastatin A4 Phosphate (CA4P)) Disodium is the water-soluble prodrug of Combretastatin A4 (CA4), which is a microtubule-targeting agent that binds β-tubulin with Kd of 0.4 μM. Fosbretabulin Disodium inhibits the polymerization of tubulin with IC50 of 2.4 μM, and also disrupts tumor vasculature. Phase 3.
HA14-1 is a non-peptidic ligand of a Bcl-2 surface pocket with IC50 of ~9 μM.
Pirarubicin is an anthracycline agent.
Agomelatine is classified as a norepinephrine-dopamine disinhibitor (NDDI) due to its antagonism of the 5-HT2C receptor.
Biperiden is an antiparkinsonian agent of the anticholinergic type.
Granisetron HCl is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist
Ondansetron HCl is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist.
Venlafaxine is an arylalkanolamine serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI).
Rizatriptan Benzoate(Maxalt) is a 5-HT1 agonist triptan drug for the treatment of migraine headaches.

Chlorprothixene has strong binding affinities to dopamine and histamine receptors, such as D1, D2, D3, D5, H1, 5-HT2, 5-HT6 and 5-HT7, with Ki of 18 nM, 2.96 nM, 4.56 nM, 9 nM, 3.75 nM, 9.4 nM, 3 nM and 5.6 nM, respectively.
Metoprolol tartrate is a cardioselective β-adrenergic receptor blocker with IC50 of 42 ng/mL.
Nefiracetam is a GABAergic, cholinergic, and monoaminergic neuronal systems enhancer for Ro 5-4864-induced convulsions. Phase 2.
Ginkgolide A is an extract from in Ginkgo biloba and a g-aminobutyric acid (GABA) antagonist with a Ki of 14.5 μM.
Inhibitor of inflammatory cytokine secretion
JSH-23 is an inhibitor of NF-κB transcriptional activity with IC50 of 7.1 μM.
Caffeic acid phenethyl ester is a potent and specific inhibitor of NF-κB activation, and also displays antioxidant, immunomodulatory and antiinflammatory activities.
Plerixafor is a chemokine receptor antagonist for CXCR4 and CXCL12-mediated chemotaxis with IC50 of 44 nM and 5.7 nM, respectively.
Nebivolol selectively inhibits β1-adrenoceptor with IC50 of 0.8 nM.
Quetiapine fumarate(Seroquel) is an atypical antipsychotic used in the treatment of schizophrenia, bipolar I mania, bipolar II depression, bipolar I depression.
Clemastine Fumarate (Clemastine) is a selective histamine H1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 3 nM.
Irsogladine is an anti-gastric ulcer agent that facilitates gap-junctional intercellular communication through M1 muscarininc acetylcholine receptor binding.
Urapidil hydrochloride is a hydrochloride salt form of urapidil which is α1-adrenoceptor antagonist and 5-HT1A receptor agonist with pIC50 of 6.13 and 6.4 respectively.
Dienogest is an orally active synthetic progesterone (or progestin).
Cetirizine DiHCl is an antihistamine.
Lidocaine is a selective inverse peripheral histamine H1-receptor agonist with an IC50 of >32 μM.
Rocuronium Bromide is an aminosteroid non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocker or muscle relaxant.
Zibotentan (ZD4054) is a specific Endothelin (ET)A antagonist with IC50 of 21 nM, exhibiting no activity at ETB. Phase 3.
Pyridostigmine Bromide is a parasympathomimetic and a reversible cholinesterase inhibitor.
Toremifene Citrate is an oral selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) which helps oppose the actions of estrogen in the body.
Dapoxetine hydrochloride is a short-acting novel selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor.
Tamoxifen Citrate is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor by competitive inhibition of estrogen binding.
Phentolamine Mesylate is a nonselective alpha-adrenergic antagonist with IC50 of 0.1 μM.
A novel platelet inhibitor
Megestrol Acetate is a synthetic progesteronal agent with an IC50 of 260 μM for the inhibition of HegG2.
Loratadine is a selective inverse peripheral histamine H1-receptor agonist with an IC50 of >32 μM.
Alfuzosin(Uroxatral) is an alpha1 receptor antagonist used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH).
Naratriptan (Amerge) is a triptan agent that is used for the treatment of migraine headaches.
Silodosin(Rapaflo) is an α1-adrenoceptor antagonist with high uroselectivity.
Ranitidine is a histamine H2-receptor antagonist with IC50 of 3.3 ± 1.4 μM.
Roxatidine Acetate HCl is a specific and competitive histamin H2-receptor antagonist, with IC50 of 3.2 μM, inhibits gastric acid secretion and ulcer formation.
Aripiprazole is a human 5-HT1A receptor partial agonist with a Ki of 4.2 nM.
Memantine hydrochloride (Namenda) is a CYP2B6 and CYP2D6 inhibitor for recombinant CYP2B6 and CYP2D6 with Ki of 0.51 nM and 94.9 μM, respectively.
Trimebutine is an agonist of peripheral mu, kappa and delta opiate receptors, used as spasmolytic agent for treatment of both acute and chronic abdominal pain.
Cisatracurium Besylate is a nondepolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent, antagonizing the action of acetylcholine by inhibiting neuromuscular transmission.
(-)-Huperzine A is a potent, highly specific and reversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) with Ki of 7 nM, exhibiting 200-fold more selectivity for G4 AChE over G1 AChE. Phase 4.
Amantadine HCl is used to treat or prevent infections of the respiratory tract caused by a certain virus.
Domperidone(Motilium) is a dopamine blocker and an antidopaminergic reagent.
Pancuronium dibromide is a competitive acetylcholine antagonist with an IC50 of 5.5 ± 0.5 nM.
Epinephrine Bitartrate is alpha- and beta-adrenergic receptor stimulator.
Tolterodine tartrate (Detrol LA) is a tartrate salt of tolterodine that is a competitive muscarinic receptor antagonist.
Mifepristone is a remarkably active antagonist of progesterone receptor and glucocorticoid receptor with IC50 of 0.2 nM and 2.6 nM, respectively.
BMY 7378 is a multi-targeted inhibitor of α2C-adrenoceptor and α1D-adrenoceptor with pKi of 6.54 and 8.2, respectively, and acts as a mixed agonist and antagonist for 5-HT1A receptor with pKi of 8.3.
Ivabradine HCl, a new If inhibitor with IC 50 of 2.9 μM which acts specifically on the pacemaker activity of the sinoatrial node, is a pure heart rate lowering agent.
Naftopidil (Flivas) is a selective α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist or alpha blocker with a Ki of 58.3 nM.
Hesperetin is a bioflavonoid and, to be more specific, a flavanone.
Amfebutamone HCl is a selective norepinephrine-dopamine reuptake inhibitor with IC50 of 6.5 and 3.4μM for the reuptake of dopamine and norepinephrine, respectively
Estriol is an antagonist of the G-protein coupled estrogen receptor in estrogen receptor-negative breast cancer cells.
Phenoxybenzamine HCl is a non-specific, irreversible alpha antagonist with an IC50 of 550 nM.
L-Adrenaline belongs to a group of the compounds known as catecholamines.
Azelastine hydrochloride (Astelin) is a potent, second-generation, selective, histamine antagonist.
Arecoline is a muscarinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.
RS-127445 is a selective 5-HT2B receptor antagonist with pKi of 9.5 and pIC50 of 10.4, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptors.
